teaser: Insig Technologies is a fast growing Mining Technology company with a newly created role for a Data Analyst.
desktopAdTemplate: Insig Technologies' innovative solutions represents the next evolutionary step in underground mining, we execute projects across Australia, as well overseas.Our MissionInsig Technologies is a leader in underground mining technology. Our mission is to partner with leading mining companies to increase their productivity and enhance safety in our client operations through leading-edge technologies and highly skilled people. About the RoleInsig Technologies is a fast growing for Mining Technology company with a newly created role for a Data Analyst. The role will be based in their head office in Perth, with potential to work remotely from anywhere across the globe, specifically Africa’s, America’s and Asia Pacific, making this a highly flexible and unique opportunity.As a Data Analyst in our Data / BI Analytics team, you will be working with key business and project stakeholders to discover and understand the data landscape which will assist with the reporting needs of a digital mining platform for an international mining organisation. The solutions will provide remote enablement and automation capability across multiple regions that will increase operational visibility and ultimately support improved decision-making across the business.  You will be utilising cloud-based technologies, gathering, designing, managing, and delivering complex data and information management platforms in areas such as business intelligence, machine learning, data mining, complex data analytics, taking a solution from strategy through implementation to managed service.In this role you can expect to work closely with Project Sponsors, Business Owners, Business Users as well as Architects, Data Scientist & Engineers, Business Analysts and Developers, using the latest industry standards to strategise, design, and deliver robust, analytics;Analyse to isolate key trends and business opportunities;Develop strong business analysis skills including Data Modelling (Conceptual, Logical and Physical) and Business Process governance frameworks, visualisations, data flows, and integrations;Building relationships and developing platform advocacy across a variety of stakeholders including internal customers, vendor and partners;Develop the ability to provide insight to new and emerging information management related best practices;Produce documentation in accordance with prevailing client standards and methodologies; andAbility to develop reports and dashboards.Skills and Qualifications:Tertiary qualified in Business, Analytics, Statistical, Mathematics or Science background preferred;At least 3+ years’ relevant work experience as an IT Data Analyst;Knowledge of the Mining technologies and Resources particularly underground mining;Experienced in data analysis, data modelling and requirements mapping;Strong analytical skills and ability to logically assess and dissect complex information or data sets in order to identify data patterns;Intellectual curiosity with the ability to question and incentives to enable the continued growth of our business and our success. teaser: This future Melbourne unicorn just closed a Series A, and we're helping them to expand their team even further.
desktopAdTemplate: Hey there, we're Crew. We're the exclusive Talent Partners for some of Melbourne's most exciting and progressive technology firms.  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Like Qsic. We love this business, not only because of their global vision and potential but mainly because of their people. They're a team of problem solvers, collaborators, thinkers and doers combined with solid technical chops. Check them out for yourself here; https://getqsic.com/ You'll get to work with some super smart people who care about each other and are focussed on building a world-class, world-first product. Their last hire is an ex-Google & Microsoft Data Scientist; that's the calibre of team we're building. They built Australia’s first commercial music streaming platform, but that was just the beginning. They’re now building the world’s first platform for fully-automated, AI-driven, patten recognition experiment design and applied to learning at scale. This will be underpinned by grassroots transactional and instore behavioural data. Simply put, they're using human curation, AI, and IoT devices to build a retail and commercial analytics platform that will help clients to understand and predict in-store customer behaviour. The Snr Back End Developer we’re hiring will be a key part of the team to build this. Based in the inner-east suburbs of Melbourne, you’ll get to do the Flexi-working thing.  Even though they’re an early-stage startup, you won't be expected to work stupid hours; there’s a really strong commitment to people getting their balance of work and home life right. There’s also a super-strong commitment to building a diverse and inclusive team so everyone is encouraged to apply. The role is going to involve;  Writing test-driven Python in an Agile environment. Building and support our backend infrastructure to support our current customer base, as we grow here at home and into other countries. Building API's and management layers for the IoT fleet that powers our customer installations, using Django. Working on existing embedded systems and the implementation of new systems, alongside our IoT team. Creating internal tooling for our customer support team. Bringing security enhancements to our current API's and embedded systems. Working with colleagues across the business on new project specifications and requirements. Designing the next iteration of our platform. Coaching other developers to assist them in integrating new ideas into the current development pipeline. Taking ideas and concepts, and turn them into new products and offerings. Working with some amazing people and have an impact on the future of Qsic.You'd most likely be our ideal candidate if;  You have solid experience of 5+ years in commercial back end engineering preferably with a strong Python focus. You have recent commercial experience working with Django and Django Rest Framework. You've worked in a Test-Driven Development environment. You have a working knowledge of CI tools (Jenkins) and Git Flow processes. You are someone who stays up-to-date with best practices and technologies and can bring these to the development team and management for discussion. You can share knowledge and teach peers and more junior developers alike. You work best when given autonomy and clear goals. One of our "nice to have, but not essential" things is experience in developing fault-tolerant applications within AWS using some or all of the following: CloudFormation, Lambda, ECS, RDS Aurora (MySQL & Postgres), Elastic Beanstalk, S3 & CloudFront is nice to haveIn return Qsic offers A competitive salary and Employee Share Option plan. Own a part of the company and share in the success. MacBook Pro, dual Dell monitors, and adjustable standing desk. A training budget for you to work on your skills. Flexible working arrangements. Room to grow as a developer, as well as teach those junior to you. Work with the latest technologies and frameworks. Great team and open environment. Have an impact on the future direction of the team.So apply now and let's get to know each other. Together we'll figure out if this could be a great match.  Everyone gets a response.

desktopAdTemplate:

Winslow Group and is a renowned civil construction provider for the residential, industrial, commercial and infrastructure sectors.

Business analytics.
Statistics.
Linear Algebra.
General Development/Coding Skills.
Engineering.
Machine Learning.

Work with large, complex data to measure results, build and develop predictive models, non-routine analysis problems, and apply advanced analytical methods as needed; Conduct end-to-end analysis that includes data gathering, data cleaning, and requirements specification processing, analysis, ongoing deliverables, and presentations.

Employ data visualization and storytelling to communicate and engage stakeholders.

Self-motivation and the ability to work independently.

Strictly, no agencies please.

teaser: In 2020 alone, our revenue went from $1.5M per annum to $25M per annum. We are looking for an energetic and passionate person to help us get to $50M.
desktopAdTemplate: About us:We are a thriving FinTech business offering microloans online. In 2020 alone, our revenue grew from $1.5M per annum to over $25M per annum. We are looking for another data scientist to add to our growing team to take our revenue in 2021 to $30-50M. We have a team of 40 people overseas (customer service and tech). In Australia, we are an executive team comprised of the managing director, our head of tech, head of data, a full stack developer and an operations manager. We are extremely tech focused and are extremely motivated to achieve great things. We want someone who strives for more in life, someone who ready to be under pressure whilst still being creative. It is incredibly fulfilling working in a company where you get to see it grow before your eyes. Help us continue to do that. Job Overview:We are looking for a Data Scientist who will support our product, sales, leadership and marketing teams with insights gained from analyzing company data. The ideal candidate is adept at using large data sets to find opportunities for product and process optimization and using models to test the effectiveness of different courses of action. They must have strong experience using a variety of data mining/data analysis methods, using a variety of data tools, building and implementing models, using/creating algorithms and creating/running simulations. They must have a proven ability to drive business results with their data-based insights. They must be comfortable working with a wide range of stakeholders and functional teams. The right candidate will have a passion for discovering solutions hidden in large data sets and working with stakeholders to improve business outcomes. Responsibilities: Work with stakeholders throughout the organization to identify opportunities for leveraging company data to drive business solutions. Mine and analyze data from company databases to drive optimization and improvement of product development, marketing techniques and business strategies. Assess the effectiveness and accuracy of new data sources and data gathering techniques. Develop custom data models and algorithms to apply to data sets. Use predictive modeling to increase and optimize customer experiences, revenue generation, ad targeting and other business outcomes. Develop company A/B testing framework and test model quality. Coordinate with different functional teams to implement models and monitor outcomes. Develop processes and tools to monitor and analyze model performance and data accuracy.Qualifications for Data Scientist: Strong problem solving skills with an emphasis on product development. Experience using statistical computer languages (R, Python, SLQ, etc.) to manipulate data and draw insights from large data sets. Experience working with and creating data architectures. Knowledge of a variety of machine learning techniques (clustering, decision tree learning, artificial neural networks, etc.) and their real-world advantages/drawbacks. Knowledge of advanced statistical techniques and concepts (regression, properties of distributions, statistical tests and proper usage, etc.) and experience with applications. Excellent written and verbal communication skills for coordinating across teams. A drive to learn and master new technologies and techniques. We’re looking for someone with 5-7 years of experience manipulating data sets and building statistical models, has a Master’s or PHD in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or another quantitative field, and is familiar with the following software/tools: Knowledge and experience in statistical and data mining techniques: GLM/Regression, Random Forest, Boosting, Trees, text mining, social network analysis, etc. Experience querying databases and using statistical computer languages: R, Python, SLQ, etc. Deployed at least 4+ models in productions used by businesses. Experience using web services: AWS, Google Cloud. Proven Experience creating and using advanced machine learning algorithms and statistics: regression, simulation, scenario analysis, modeling, clustering, decision trees, neural networks, etc. Experience analyzing data from 3rd party providers: Google Analytics, Site Catalyst, Coremetrics, Adwords, Crimson Hexagon, Facebook Insights, etc. Experience visualizing/presenting data for stakeholders.

teaser: An exciting opportunity exists for a Language Data Scientist to support the School of Languages and Cultures
desktopAdTemplate:
School of Languages and Cultures 
The School of Languages and Cultures has grown rapidly in recent years and now has over 1000 equivalent full-time students (over 8,000 course enrolments). It is one of the largest schools of language instruction in Australia with 46 fixed-term and continuing academic staff.
The School of Languages and Cultures teaches Chinese, French, German, Indonesian, Japanese, Korean, Russian and Spanish, as well as Linguistics and Applied Linguistics, to students in the Bachelor of Arts, Bachelor of International Studies, and the University-wide concurrent Diploma in Languages, the Diploma of Arts, and dual degree programs.
At postgraduate level, the School offers two NAATI-accredited Masters programs in Translation and Interpreting (one in Japanese and one in Chinese) and growing programs in Linguistics, Applied Linguistics and TESOL. Staff research and supervise PhD students in these fields and also in Australian Aboriginal languages.
About This Opportunity
We currently have an excellent opportunity for a Language Data Scientist to join the School of Languages and Cultures. The Language Technology and Data Analysis Lab (LADAL) in the School of Languages and Cultures is driving the development of a series of national eResearch infrastructure projects, including the Australian Text Analytics Platform (ATAP) and the Language Data Commons of Australia (LDaCA), in collaboration with the NCRIS-funded Australian Research Data Commons (ARDC) and other key national partner institutions.
The primary purpose of this position is to provide support for building and utilising the digital research platforms and tools developed through these projects, including supporting the training of researchers in the use of these platforms and tools, and to engage in research on the development and use of language technologies.
This position is located at our picturesque St Lucia campus, renowned as one of Australia’s most attractive university campuses, and located just 7km from Brisbane’s city centre. Bounded by the Brisbane River on three sides, and with outstanding public transport connections, our 114-hectare site provides a perfect work environment – you can enjoy the best of both worlds: a vibrant campus with the tradition of an established university.
Our Ideal Candidate
Alongside the completion of a PhD in an area of Language Technology or related field, or significant progress towards such a qualification, the successful candidate will demonstrate the following:
Successful Level A candidates will demonstrate:
Demonstrated evidence of a developing record of publication in high-quality outlets in the field.
Demonstrated skills in common programming languages, including Python and R.
Evidence of ongoing research projects, including plans for external funding applications.
In addition to the essentials for Level A above, Level B candidates must have the following:
Demonstrated evidence of an established record of publication in high-quality outlets in the field.
Evidence of ongoing research projects, including plans for external funding applications.
For a full list of duties and selection criteria, please see the attached Position Description.
You must have unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this appointment to apply. Visa sponsorship is not available for this appointment.
We value diversity and inclusion, and actively encourage applications from those who bring diversity to the University. Our Diversity and Inclusion webpage contains further information if you require additional support. Accessibility requirements and/or adjustments can be directed to recruitment@uq.edu.au.
What We Can Offer
This is a full-time, fixed term position for 3 years at Academic Level A/B (level of appointment will be commensurate with qualifications, experience and academic achievements).
The full-time equivalent base salary at Level A will be in the range $70,729 - $94,637, plus super of up to 17%. The total FTE package will be in the range $82,752 - $110,725
The full-time equivalent base salary at Level B will be in the range $99,542 - $118,206, plus super of up to 17%. The total FTE package will be in the range $116,465 - $138,301
You will be able to take advantage of UQ Sport Facilities, salary sacrificing options, on-campus childcare, discounted private health insurance, cheap parking, development programs and many other benefits.
For further information, please review The University of Queensland's Enterprise Bargaining Agreement 2018-2021.

Questions?
To discuss this role please contact Professor Michael Haugh, Professor, School of Languages and Cultures via michael.haugh@uq.edu.au.
For application queries, please contact recruitment@uq.edu.au stating the job number in the subject line.
Want to Apply?
To submit an application for this role, use the apply button. All applicants must supply the following documents:
Cover letter
Resume
Responses to the Selection Criteria (in the attached PD)
To satisfy pre-requisite questions and ensure your application can be considered in full, all candidates must apply via the UQJobs portal by the job closing deadline. Applications received via other channels including direct email will not be accepted.
Interviews Tentatively Scheduled: TBC
Applications Close: 28 May 2021 at 11:00PM AEST

teaser: These roles are permanent positions in our Methodology Division and Data Strategies, Integration and Services Division.
desktopAdTemplate: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to fill several Assistant Director (EL1) positions including Mathematical Statistician, Data Scientist, Data Collection Methodologist, Data Consultant, Data Governance Officer and Data Engineer.   The roles are permanent positions, available as full-time or part-time, to be filled in the Canberra, Sydney, Melbourne, Geelong, Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide ABS offices.About the RolesRoles in the Methodology DivisionWe are seeking motivated people with skills in fields such as statistics, data science, mathematics, modelling and analysis, survey sampling and estimation, questionnaire design and evaluation, statistical disclosure control, statistical data integration, economics / econometrics or time series analysis (tertiary qualifications highly desirable). The roles are best suited to people who are able to manage staff and work well in a team environment, have strong problem-solving skills, and are able to work flexibly to agreed priorities and deadlines. A career in MD will provide opportunities to develop expertise in methods used in the conduct of official statistics, and opportunities to develop and adapt new methods to be used in the ABS in the future. Successful applicants will have future opportunities to be transferred or promoted within MD or move to other interesting roles across the ABS.The positions offer flexible working arrangements (in terms of hours and/or doing some work from home), working in virtual teams (across the country) and collaborating with external methodologists and other experts in academia, other government agencies or overseas in other National Statistical Offices.Roles in the Data Strategies, Integration and Services DivisionData Consultants connect customers to data. They are highly responsive to stakeholders, including the Australian public, seeking to ensure that their customers have effective and safe access to a wide range of data and statistics. They collaborate across their networks within the ABS and externally to address their customers’ needs, by releasing high quality customised aggregate data, facilitating access to microdata, or by providing their customers with the tools and knowledge to meet their own data needs. Data Consultants may specialise in a particular subject matter area (e.g. Health Statistics; Construction Statistics, integrated data) or may work across a wide range of ABS data.Data Governance Officers provide high quality data governance and program assurance. They achieve this through a range of activities including: developing data integration policy and strategy; designing and implementing processes and procedures to increase access to data while ensuring it is kept safe; contributing to maintaining the trust of data custodians and other stakeholders; and providing strategic and operational governance support to the division, ensuring accountability and transparency. Data Governance Officers apply a strong understanding of confidentiality and privacy principles and the ABS legislative framework. Data Engineers provide a reliable infrastructure for data. Data Engineers configure and lead the production processes used in the preparation, transformation, integration and testing of data, so that it can be safely and effectively used by internal and external customers in statistical analysis and statistical and data products and services. They design, develop and maintain software architectures to collect and analyse large datasets. They may support collection of, or work with, data from a broad range of sources, including surveys, census, and administrative sources. Data Engineers must apply a strong understanding of confidentiality and privacy principles, the ABS legislative framework, and ABS data release policies.How to apply: Click the apply now button to apply and to find out more about these positions. This will re-direct you to the ABS website to submit your application online.Applications close at 11:30PM AEST on Wednesday 19 May 2021.

Data Consultants may specialise in a particular subject matter area (e.g. Health Statistics; Construction Statistics, integrated data) or may work across a wide range of ABS data.Data Governance Officers provide high quality data governance and program assurance. They achieve this through a range of activities including: developing data integration policy and strategy; designing and implementing processes and procedures to increase access to data while ensuring it is kept safe; contributing to maintaining the trust of data custodians and other stakeholders; and providing strategic and operational governance support to the division, ensuring accountability and transparency. Data Governance Officers apply a strong understanding of confidentiality and privacy principles and the ABS legislative framework. Data Engineers provide a reliable infrastructure for data. Data Engineers configure and lead the production processes used in the preparation, transformation, integration and testing of data, so that it can be safely and effectively used by internal and external customers in statistical analysis and statistical and data products and services. They design, develop and maintain software architectures to collect and analyse large datasets. They may support collection of, or work with, data from a broad range of sources, including surveys, census, and administrative sources. Data Engineers must apply a strong understanding of confidentiality and privacy principles, the ABS legislative framework, and ABS data release policies.How to apply: Click the apply now button to apply and to find out more about these positions. This will re-direct you to the ABS website to submit your application online.Applications close at 11:30PM AEST on Wednesday 19 May 2021.

Data Engineers must apply a strong understanding of confidentiality and privacy principles, the ABS legislative framework, and ABS data release policies.How to apply: Click the apply now button to apply and to find out more about these positions. This will re-direct you to the ABS website to submit your application online.Applications close at 11:30PM AEST on Wednesday 19 May 2021.

teaser: These roles are permanent positions in our Methodology Division and Data Strategies, Integration and Services Division.
desktopAdTemplate: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to fill several Assistant Director (EL1) positions including Mathematical Statistician, Data Scientist, Data Collection Methodologist, Data Consultant, Data Governance Officer and Data Engineer.   The roles are permanent positions, available as full-time or part-time, to be filled in the Canberra, Sydney, Melbourne, Geelong, Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide ABS offices.About the RolesRoles in the Methodology DivisionWe are seeking motivated people with skills in fields such as statistics, data science, mathematics, modelling and analysis, survey sampling and estimation, questionnaire design and evaluation, statistical disclosure control, statistical data integration, economics / econometrics or time series analysis (tertiary qualifications highly desirable). The roles are best suited to people who are able to manage staff and work well in a team environment, have strong problem-solving skills, and are able to work flexibly to agreed priorities and deadlines. A career in MD will provide opportunities to develop expertise in methods used in the conduct of official statistics, and opportunities to develop and adapt new methods to be used in the ABS in the future. Successful applicants will have future opportunities to be transferred or promoted within MD or move to other interesting roles across the ABS.The positions offer flexible working arrangements (in terms of hours and/or doing some work from home), working in virtual teams (across the country) and collaborating with external methodologists and other experts in academia, other government agencies or overseas in other National Statistical Offices.Roles in the Data Strategies, Integration and Services DivisionData Consultants connect customers to data. They are highly responsive to stakeholders, including the Australian public, seeking to ensure that their customers have effective and safe access to a wide range of data and statistics. They collaborate across their networks within the ABS and externally to address their customers’ needs, by releasing high quality customised aggregate data, facilitating access to microdata, or by providing their customers with the tools and knowledge to meet their own data needs. Data Consultants may specialise in a particular subject matter area (e.g. Health Statistics; Construction Statistics, integrated data) or may work across a wide range of ABS data.Data Governance Officers provide high quality data governance and program assurance. They achieve this through a range of activities including: developing data integration policy and strategy; designing and implementing processes and procedures to increase access to data while ensuring it is kept safe; contributing to maintaining the trust of data custodians and other stakeholders; and providing strategic and operational governance support to the division, ensuring accountability and transparency. Data Governance Officers apply a strong understanding of confidentiality and privacy principles and the ABS legislative framework. Data Engineers provide a reliable infrastructure for data. Data Engineers configure and lead the production processes used in the preparation, transformation, integration and testing of data, so that it can be safely and effectively used by internal and external customers in statistical analysis and statistical and data products and services. They design, develop and maintain software architectures to collect and analyse large datasets. They may support collection of, or work with, data from a broad range of sources, including surveys, census, and administrative sources. Data Engineers must apply a strong understanding of confidentiality and privacy principles, the ABS legislative framework, and ABS data release policies.How to apply: Click the apply now button to apply and to find out more about these positions. This will re-direct you to the ABS website to submit your application online.Applications close at 11:30PM AEST on Wednesday 19 May 2021.

teaser: Analytics Translator Top ASX Listed Company Great Company Culture and Flexible Working
desktopAdTemplate: Analytics Translator required by a top ASX listed organization, taking a key strategic position across the full business enterprise you will be the bridge between data science and the business. With your knowledge and understanding of both analytical and commercial / operational disciplines, you’ll help business leaders identify and prioritize their business problems, based on which will create the highest value when solved. You’re both business savvy and analytics proficient able to frame a problem, shape a solution, and champion change. As a translator, you will be the link between the business and the data scientists, defining complex data-related requirements that bring strategic priorities to life. The role is based in the Melbourne CBD, offering a very competitive remuneration package, flexible working environment and a great company culture. Key responsibilities  Identifying sources of value from data analytics across core business domains (such as marketing, risk, and operations) and to define paths realizing that value Help to identify most impactful insights from modelling for business and communicate them clearly and concisely Ensure that the deep insights generated through sophisticated analytics translate into impact at scale in an organization Run commercial sizing and feasibility management and articulate and sizing opportunities Work with data scientist and data engineer to give a real world view to the data and analytics to ensure fit for purpose design of new products and services You will lead projects and where necessary supervise daily activities of the team membersWhat you’ll bring: A strong commercial background and proven ability to spot opportunity and size it Have a financial or mathematical background but primarily with commercial experience, or transfer from data science with technical fluency A true believer and practitioner in the power of data and AI, the value of scientific evidence-based learning and accumulated incremental wins Have process-management skills to direct an analytics initiative from ideation to production Ideally some people management experience Familiarity with machine-learning technologies and tools, such as big data stack, Python, R and visulaisation techniques Finally have an entrepreneurial spirit. Enthusiasm, commitment, drive and business savvy to navigate the many potential roadblocks

teaser: Tap into the expertise of the company brand, and work on limitless opportunities within the data science field across several industries.
desktopAdTemplate: Apply your deep expertise in data science, machine learning and consulting skills in end-to-end client engagementsWork with innovative teams and the latest technologiesJoin a business that takes action across diversity and inclusion within teamsAbout the Culture Inclusive and innovative workspace and workforce that will accept you for you and not expect you to fit a "cookie cutter mould"Amazing repuation in the market for their delivery and expertise in data science, so learning from anyone in this team would really elevate your skills quicklyBusiness strategies are people and culture centric, as they believe that a successful business is nothing without good peopleAbout the RoleCombine AI with data, analytics and automation under a strategic vision to transform businessesArticulate business impact and benefits of advanced analytics solutions via business/scientific storytelling and advanced visualisation techniquesDesign, build, develop and apply solutions that interpret human speech and translate Present insightful and value adding solutions to a variety of different clients in the market Experience Required3 + years commercial experience in an advanced analytics/data science roleYou must have - SQL skills, visualisation skills, cloud experience, R or Python OR both and the ability to tell a story with dataEducation in either of the following; Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Operations Research, Computer Science, Engineering, Economics or similarExperience in financial services/banking industry is highly regarded Strong communicator and the confidence to present to clients This position can be based in MELBOURNE OR SYDNEY. teaser: Exciting opportunities exist at the AP5 and APS6 levels as policy advisers for the Policy Implementation Committee team, and data scientists/analysts
desktopAdTemplate: The Opportunity:  We are recruiting for two separate teams within the branch: policy advisers for the Policy Implementation Committee team, and data scientists/analysts for the Central Analytics Hub. Candidates are able to select preferences for the different roles.Policy Implementation Committee team (Adviser)The Priorities and Delivery Unit (PDU) within Cabinet Division is seeking advisers for a number of positions across PDU. We operate in a dynamic environment at the heart of government, providing a range of functions to ensure the smooth functioning of the Cabinet and its Committees as well as supporting analytical data work and visualisation. The work is interesting and challenging, often fast-paced and has a high degree of autonomy and visibility, within PM&C and across Government.The positions are ideal for candidates wishing to build their knowledge and understanding of the Cabinet process. Experience in a Cabinet Division role will position you well for future career development and is extremely well-regarded by many areas across PM&C and Government.You will have the opportunity to work with highly skilled and experienced colleagues and leaders in a supportive and collaborative work environment. The skills required range across policy advising, writing for various audiences, coordination and liaison and secretariat work.Central Analytics Hub (Data Scientist/Analyst)The Central Analytics Hub is the core data science team at the Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet. We are a close-knit, multidisciplinary team that works on a combination of longer-term analytical research and urgent, high-stakes data manipulation and analysis. We use data, code and automation to answer questions for very senior decision makers. It’s a well-resourced, fast-paced environment where we balance delivering results quickly and reliably with continual improvement and skills development. Our team solves problems by focusing on three core pillars of work: building data tools, advising on data processes, and analysing data for insights.The Central Analytics Hub within PDU is looking for an enthusiastic, pragmatic and experienced data scientist/analyst with experience in data engineering. The role is fast paced, varied and presents an exciting opportunity to provide analysis and insights to senior decision makers in government.We are often called-on on short notice, so some work outside normal hours may be required (which will be compensated). Our Ideal Candidates: Our ideal candidate will be a problem-solver with the ability to develop professional relationships with a broad range of stakeholders. All roles require sound judgement and discretion, as well as attention to detail, in working with sensitive and privileged information. Flexibility and resilience will enable you to thrive in this fast-paced work environment. We are seeking candidates with a range of experience.Policy Implementation Committee teamFor Policy Implementation Committee team roles, our ideal candidate will perform a range of duties, including: Supporting departments to develop high quality Cabinet material and other matters for Cabinet consideration Providing advice on a range of Cabinet arrangements and processes Liaising and collaborating with stakeholders across the APS and beyond to gather information and track the progress of policy development and implementation. Analysing, reporting and visualising data and information to generate performance insights and inform policy decision making. Generating practical solutions to complex policy problems, in addition to identifying opportunities and proposing innovations to improve the status quo. Communicating results and advice to the Prime Minister, Cabinet and PM&C executive through a variety of mediums, including briefs and placemats.The ideal candidate will have: Excellent communication, interpersonal and relationship management skills, including the ability to work collaboratively, persuade, influence and negotiate both within and outside of government. Excellent analytical and problem solving skills, and the intellectual curiosity to explore complex questions and opportunities to improve existing conditions. Data literacy skills, including the ability to evaluate performance using data-driven evidence and to communicate key insights effectively. Strategic judgement, flexibility and resilience to manage competing priorities in a dynamic, fast-paced environment. Sound understanding of government and Cabinet processes.Central Analytics HubFor Central Analytics Hub data scientist/analyst roles:Our ideal candidate will enjoy solving technical problems, working in a highly dynamic environment and building the team’s capabilities. They will bring an understanding of social and economic policy and the application of quantitative methods to answer policy questions.Our ideal candidate will be part of a dynamic team conducting analytical projects, building the Department’s data capabilities and reporting on high-profile issues to the Prime Minister. Our ideal candidate will demonstrate strategic thinking and be able to translate complex analysis into meaningful insights for time-poor APS leaders.Key responsibilities will involve automation (including data flows, briefing outputs & team processes), wrangling and scraping data (including from websites and documents) and building best practices within the team. You will deliver high-quality analysis to decision makers in PM&C. Our ideal candidate will also advise other areas in the APS on data processes, which requires strong communication skills and a knack for building and maintaining relationships.Skills and demonstrable experience should include: a demonstrated ability to manage time and work in fast-paced environments, and to pragmatically achieve results that are reliable and accurate proficiency in an analytical computer language (e.g. R or Python) and experience developing advanced, functional code that is clean, efficient, re-usable and readable in a fast paced and changing environment a willingness to evaluate, learn and teach new technologies an ability to convey technical information to suit different audiences excellent communication skills (both written and spoken), especially demonstrated skills in communicating complex technical information to a variety of audiences quickly developed stakeholder engagement skills, including the ability to influence stakeholders, and build and maintain strong relationships with across PM&C and the APS strategic thinking in the context of public administration and policy, and a curiosity about how data science can contribute to policy questionsDesirable skills include: experience with any or all of: Azure DevOps, continuous integration, unit testing, Docker, Rocker and containerization, Linux bash, git, SQL, environment management (such as ‘renv’ or ‘drake’), R Shiny the application of data analysis methods such as regression, machine learning, or other quantitative methods to microdata experience working with policy areas to specify needs and deliver client-ready productsThe merit pool established through this selection process will not be shared until all vacancies within Cabinet Division have been filled.   What We Offer: A flexible, diverse and inclusive workplace and attractive remuneration package including generous employer superannuation contributions, Exciting and fulfilling work including career development and networking opportunities,  The opportunity to work with strong, smart, visionary and experienced leaders who encourage and support you to develop your interests and expertise and achieve your ambitions.  Eligibility:  To be eligible for employment with PM&C, applicants must be an Australian Citizen at the time of the vacancy closing.Applicants must be able to obtain and maintain a NV1 security clearance, or hold a current security clearance of an appropriate level.   How to apply: If this sounds like the opportunity you are looking for, we want to hear from you!  Submit an online application through the  PM&C Careers Page by Monday, 24 May 2021 at 11:30pm AEDT.

teaser: Incredible opportunity for a passionate and highly driven Senior Python Engineer who is looking to join a rapidly-expanding fintech startup
desktopAdTemplate: About UsRich Data Corporation is a rapidly expanding, dynamic start-up based in Sydney. We use data and predictive analytics combined with artificial intelligence technology with deep knowledge in behaviour analysis to deliver innovative lending solutions for financial services and adjacent industries through our Delta platform. Our vision is to enable lenders to innovate and achieve highly profitable lending outcomes while providing inclusive credit options to consumers and SME.  Why Join Us?This is an opportunity to join an organisation with a global footprint that is still small enough to be agile.Work with the leadership team to help drive the future of credit.Work with our world class research team to productise cutting edge AI innovations.Dynamic and friendly working environment.Our office is based in North Sydney with a great view overlooking the harbour.Flexible working environment.Competitive salary, $100,000 - $140,000, could be higher based on experience. About the roleAs the Senior Developer it’s essential that you are able to see the "big picture" as you’ll be taking the lead in designing, coding, testing and providing architecture direction from design choices to technical standards. In this role you will be working on the design, development and implementation of financial services solutions using your advanced Python experience combined with AI and Machine Learning algorithms provided by our Data scientist. Key accountabilitiesAssume technical responsibility for all stages of the software development lifecycle.Design and develop specifications and solutions with attention to system integration and data management.Execute testing to improve the quality and reduce operational risk of the developed solution.Provide technical guidance and coaching to the development team from conception to deployment.Provide on-going operational support of developed solutions to reduce the impact of application defects and related incidents. Key challengesDesign and implement complex enterprise-level solutions.Work with clients and teams distributed across multiple time zones.Constantly evaluate, learn and apply new technologies and new development techniques. Skills & experienceStrong knowledge of and practical software development experience in Python and application of AI/ML experience, e.g. model training and testing, for commercial production systems. Strong knowledge of application architecture and design principles including API design, REST, WS-*, SOA, Microservices, OOP, SOLID.Familiar with UML and other modelling methods in preparation of detailed specifications.In-depth knowledge and experience with data modelling and database design of relational and NoSQL database systems.Understanding of software quality assurance principles with experience implementing automated testing platforms and unit tests, Test Driven Development (TDD) and other agile methodologies.Interest in exploring new programming paradigms, languages, and patterns and a passion for growing your skills, tackling interesting work and challenging problems.Outstanding communication and presentation abilities.DevOps and AWS experience is highly regarded.Full stack with Java is highly regarded. Apply Now!If you have the relevant skills and are ready to take the next step in your career please apply via SEEK with your resume and cover letter attached!Email: junlong.zhai@richdataco.com [link removed] Please note candidates must have Australian working rights

teaser: Flexible start in June/July. Exciting phase of growth as we are starting a new team. Applications close 11:59pm, 30th May 2021 AEST.
desktopAdTemplate: About us Hi there, we're The Lookout Way and we build a care management platform that powers approved aged care and registered NDIS service providers, like FiveGoodFriends, our in-house care company. Our software and data signals supports our partners to get exceptional outcomes for their clients and workers. Good people using friendly software supported by data is how we do care differently and the reason why our partners are invited back into people's homes 17,000+ times a month. We're looking for a Data Analytics Engineer to join our Data Signals Team. You'll be forming part of new team of data experts that sits with 18 friendly software engineers and product designers who work remotely within Australia. We're aiming for a flexible start in June/July. Please do not apply through SEEK. See "How to apply".  About the job You'll be working as a Data Analytics Engineer to support our partners to get high signals from their data inside our care management platform, Lookout. Lookout was spun out of our in-house care business, Five Good Friends, to lift outcomes all across Australia. We structure our work around prioritised data initiatives for work of a material size, with an ad-hoc component for smaller requests. You'll partner with your fellow data analytics engineer, a product manager, and a data scientist to deliver shaped initiatives. The work is a blend of communication, analytics and data pipelining giving you the control to balance delivery and trade-offs. We do data modelling and analysis to help solve real business problems in an automated way. We use 'dbt' and 'dagster', which streamlines our data flows to minimise engineering overhead. If you haven't worked with these tools, it's ok, as we are happy to help guide you to get up and running with them. Our projects are paced into four week cycles. We spend the first 3 weeks designing and building. We spend the last week communicating the results and for anything that helps make us more efficient. You'll shape data flows using SQL and Python, and you'll craft delightful experiences for stakeholders in Sisense (Formerly Periscope) with the R/Python extension. It's a broad spectrum so we don't expect you to be the expert in all areas. Instead, you'll be complimented by a team that's inclusive, kind, and flexible to help you learn and grow. People are the heart of what we do. We don't hide behind our desk, but are pro-active in seeking the right opportunities to make a difference to real people's lives using data. We are here to help improve the Aged Care and NDIS schemes, and any other care models customers adopt through our Lookout Platform. For our greatest dashboards and models, we will look to scale these to more people by embedding the analytics within our app. Data Signals is broad and can be thought of as an analytics function backend by the latest tools and technologies to send the right messages to the right people at the right times, to enable people to be their best. We also need to tell compelling data stories so that we can help our stakeholders interpret what the data is telling us. To try and give you a better idea of Data Signals and the work we do here are some recent examples: Analytics:  Do statistical analysis to dig into a question and discover correlations between Acuity health decline and product changes.   Do a powerpoint presentation to communicate insights in everyday language   Design and build dashboard metrics to support our stakeholders   Prove or disprove an A/B hypothesis that a new product feature isn't being used by a cohort   Build a dashboard to help leaders evaluate the take up and effectiveness of a new service offering.   Perform and publish a deep dive analysis on Cancelled Home Visits   Analysis retention reasons and find data points or insights to trigger new team workflows.   Build a predictive model in Python based on Natural Language inputs   Take part in a team product & data workshop Data Engineering  Test code and outputs for accuracy and publishing the metrics to our current tools that support this (Slack, dbt, Dagster, Datadog)   Perform routine maintenance on our infrastructure. E.g. Dbt upgrade   Action an infrastructure alert using dbt in the data warehouse and creating/merging a GIT PR.   Design and build a better data model to help facilitate better repeatable analysis on a topic   Build a sensible data flow in Dagster to schedule Python work If you only have experience in some of these areas but not all of them, we would still love to hear from you. What we are after is team players who are happy and hungry to learn, unite behind our mission and work together to achieve great things for Aged Care, NDIS and other social Care models using data. It's ok if there is an area of the process you naturally gravititate towards, but we need team players who are pro-active and happy to pitch in and do their share to help. This includes a willingness to dive in and try new things, e.g. using bash command line if you are traditionally more of a front-end communicator, or thinking more deeply about a business concept if you have traditionally worked in data flows and infrastructure. About you Using data to drive good in the world motivates you. You're either a great generalist or dedicated specialist at heart and take pragmatic steps to design and implement your projects. You keep sight of the bigger picture, always working toward it and helping others see it too. You also have great written/verbal communication skills, and like a healthy balance between focusing on your tasks and collaborating. You believe in the collective outcomes of your team. When your team delivers something, we all delivered it. When you failed, we all failed and share what we learnt. We celebrate the highs and we learn from the lows. We lean on each other and we look up to each other. We're kind, honest, and flexible with each other. We invite debate and we encourage alternative perspectives, but when we commit, we put our differences aside and we see it through. You'll make hundreds of important decisions over the course of a working week. No one will prescribe low level tasks to you, but you'll know your goals. We make the time to experiment and the time to share our insights, and accept failure as part of the road to success. We also maintain healthy engagement with our leaders and stakeholders across the business, and invite dialogue to discuss the results of analysis and engage with real business problems. We also work with our partner teammates in Product to help us facilitate this shared understanding. You'll work remotely from anywhere in Australia as long as you have a solid internet connection and a comfortable setup. We do have a COVID-safe office in the Brisbane CBD, but you won't be required to work from there. Many of us are outside Brisbane. We strongly encourage candidates of all different backgrounds and identities to apply. Each new person is an opportunity for us to bring a different perspective into the team. We are committed to building an inclusive workplace where you can do your best and most rewarding work. You'll be working with vulnerable people so we require you to complete a National Police Check and the NDIS Worker Orientation Module. You must have the right to work in Australia. About our pay and perks This is a permanent, full-time position and depending on your skills and experience we're prepared to offer you a salary up to $110000 - $140000 + 9.5% Super, no matter where you live in Australia. You'll also get a $4,500 budget to pick your laptop, adapters, and display. The way we work and the perks we offer are designed to help you live a fulfilling life. Some of us start late and some of us finish early. Some of us work in big blocks and some of us break it up. We overlap for most of the day and we work a regular week where overtime is a rarity. The work we do is meaningful and the problems we solve are interesting. We like coming to work and working together, but we're 18 people who are also parents, carers, siblings, friends, students, athletes, and hobbyists with a life away from work too. You'll get the standard four weeks of paid annual leave and the standard ten days of paid personal leave. You'll also get an extra day of paid annual leave for each year you're with us after completing your second year. You'll get a yearly $500 well-being allowance to spend on anything that betters your life away from work. Some of the things we've used our allowances on are running shoes, remedial massages, gym memberships, books, and dancing classes. How to Apply To give you an idea of how we hire, these are the steps the two successful candidates will take:  Do not apply through SEEK. Apply through BeApplied https://app.beapplied.com/apply/qgyssfi5ha   First interview over a video call   Small, take-home project (We'll give you a $150 Coles gift card to partially subsidise your time)   We may have a second interview over a video call   Offer   Referee and background checks   Start on a Thursday in June/July We're grateful for your time and looking forward to hearing from you.

When your team delivers something, we all delivered it. When you failed, we all failed and share what we learnt. We celebrate the highs and we learn from the lows. We lean on each other and we look up to each other. We're kind, honest, and flexible with each other. We invite debate and we encourage alternative perspectives, but when we commit, we put our differences aside and we see it through. You'll make hundreds of important decisions over the course of a working week. No one will prescribe low level tasks to you, but you'll know your goals. We make the time to experiment and the time to share our insights, and accept failure as part of the road to success. We also maintain healthy engagement with our leaders and stakeholders across the business, and invite dialogue to discuss the results of analysis and engage with real business problems. We also work with our partner teammates in Product to help us facilitate this shared understanding. You'll work remotely from anywhere in Australia as long as you have a solid internet connection and a comfortable setup. We do have a COVID-safe office in the Brisbane CBD, but you won't be required to work from there. Many of us are outside Brisbane. We strongly encourage candidates of all different backgrounds and identities to apply. Each new person is an opportunity for us to bring a different perspective into the team. We are committed to building an inclusive workplace where you can do your best and most rewarding work. You'll be working with vulnerable people so we require you to complete a National Police Check and the NDIS Worker Orientation Module. You must have the right to work in Australia. About our pay and perks This is a permanent, full-time position and depending on your skills and experience we're prepared to offer you a salary up to $110000 - $140000 + 9.5% Super, no matter where you live in Australia. You'll also get a $4,500 budget to pick your laptop, adapters, and display. The way we work and the perks we offer are designed to help you live a fulfilling life. Some of us start late and some of us finish early. Some of us work in big blocks and some of us break it up. We overlap for most of the day and we work a regular week where overtime is a rarity. The work we do is meaningful and the problems we solve are interesting. We like coming to work and working together, but we're 18 people who are also parents, carers, siblings, friends, students, athletes, and hobbyists with a life away from work too. You'll get the standard four weeks of paid annual leave and the standard ten days of paid personal leave. You'll also get an extra day of paid annual leave for each year you're with us after completing your second year. You'll get a yearly $500 well-being allowance to spend on anything that betters your life away from work. Some of the things we've used our allowances on are running shoes, remedial massages, gym memberships, books, and dancing classes. How to Apply To give you an idea of how we hire, these are the steps the two successful candidates will take:  Do not apply through SEEK. Apply through BeApplied https://app.beapplied.com/apply/qgyssfi5ha   Applications close 11:59pm, 30th May 2021 AEST   First interview over a video call   Small, take-home project (We'll give you a $150 Coles gift card to partially subsidise your time)   We may have a second interview over a video call   Offer   Referee and background checks   Start on a Thursday in June/July We're grateful for your time and looking forward to hearing from you.

teaser: Family Zone are searching for a Data Scientist / ML Engineer, responsible for designing, developing, testing, and deploying software solutions.
desktopAdTemplate: The roleAs a Data Scientist / ML Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, testing, and deploying software solutions which address the needs of our customers, providing rich analysis and reporting and which meet the requirements of parents and schools. Your objective will be to harness the data we collect on internet use and online behaviour to provide insightful reports and event driven alerting for our customers.  Most importantly, you will be a valued member of an excellent engineering team, and the changes you make will be used by customers in homes and schools around the globe.Skills and ExperienceProven experience working in a data science role with exposure to algorithm development, ML techniques and data wrangling/sorting;Experience with natural language processing and human factor classification/heuristics;Ability to work independently and make recommendations on further tech choices;Not simply maths/analytics focused but also have the ability to code and create end to end proof of concepts where necessary;A passion for building quality software and owning solutions;You put yourself in the customer’s shoes when thinking about a problem and its solution;Open-minded and adaptable in responding to new challenges and opportunities;You demonstrate a love for continually learning and improving your skills and knowledge. Who we areFamily Zone is a fast growing tech start-up, with offices in Perth, Melbourne, NZ, and the USA. We're listed on the ASX and we are rolling out our parental control platform globally. We are passionate about software development and believe our platform will make the internet a safer place for kids and families across the world.What can Family Zone offer you?Exposure to modern technologies and processes in a fast-paced and supportive environment, working within a great development team;An opportunity to work on technology and data scaling challenges for a global customer base;The opportunity to own your changes end-to-end, from design right the way through to delivery to the customer;Opportunities to attend local software conferences, paid for by Family Zone;The chance to be part of a growing business with big goals;Support with flexible working, such as work from home options;A passionate team with a great culture;Brand new office with 'end of trip' facilities, collaborative workspaces, free fruit and Friday drinks.What’s our technology stack?Our platform is predominantly cloud-based (AWS & GCP), and we have a rich tapestry of architectural components and processes including, on the application side:RESTful backend services (Java, Python, Node.js, Go);Client-side static apps (React, Bootstrap, Backbone, AngularJS);Fit-for-purpose filtering clients deployed across laptops, mobiles and tablets (Go, Java, Kotlin, C/C++, Swift);Data processing on a petabyte scale, managing ongoing performance and scaling requirements for growth into millions of users;Database technologies, both RDBMS and NoSQL;Deployment and orchestration via Ansible, Docker, Kubernetes;Distributed version control via Git and build management via TeamCity / Bamboo;VPN servers, firmware & low-level packet inspection.For Data engineering, we use:Internally developed system of statistic and metadata reporting from our clients (agents running on various platforms) and reporting to our collections API;GCP Pub/Sub, Dataflow, Bigquery, GCS ingestion and storage pipeline;Internally developed python services for ML and analysis.We have a number of initiatives in our roadmap to extend these data and reporting processes, and envisage a combination of ‘off the shelf’ cloud enabled solutions augmented with models and solutions we develop internally.TO APPLY: https://familyzone.bamboohr.com/jobs/view.php?id=46&source=aWQ9MjE%3D [link removed] Shortlisting will commence immediately. Candidates must be eligible to work in Australia, and successful candidates will be required to obtain a current police clearance.

teaser: Exciting opportunity for a Data Scientist to embark in a journey with a disruptive start-up in interactive analytics specialised in Energy Markets!
desktopAdTemplate: About the Company Our client is a rapidly growing analytics & advisory company in the clean energy sector. Passionate about technology and renewable energy, this bubbly, small team of nerds has developed the 1st interactive analytics platform of the National Electricity Market to provide high-level decision-making insights to developers and investors and thus helping them making smarter investment decisions.  The Role Reporting directly to the Managing Director, The Data Scientist will primarily work on the platform but will also contribute to the modelling and analysis as part of their consulting services. Or get in touch with Ilan Sebban for more details - ilan@anavo.com

teaser: We are looking for highly skilled data scientist at Senior or Principal level with extensive industry experience and a track record of R&D in industry
desktopAdTemplate:
Can you work to solve our clients’ toughest analytical problems, continually pushing forward the state of the art in Computer Vision, Deep Learning and ML.
My clients' Senior Data Scientists are exposed to some of the toughest challenges and market leading innovations. As such, you will be responsible for ensuring data best practices, model choice and building, statistical result interpretation and produce numbered and visual evidence along with image recognition to support decision making at the highest levels.
 
My client is a Global leader in image recognition with plenty of variety in work and opportunities to advance your career (locally and globally). People are treated like adults here and you'll get to create a flexible working dynamic best suited to your requirements. 
 
Essential:
·Programming/Tech Environments: Ability to code in scientific python, using a Linux environment, and git for source control. Commitment to software engineering principles, a keen eye for clean code, and a passion for robustness and correctness.
·Software Engineering: Working on shared codebases to produce production quality code. 
·Domain Knowledge – Computer Vision: Machine Learning techniques applied to image data.
·Deep Learning: Commercial experience working with Tensorflow or Pytorch and designing custom architectures and bespoke training methodologies.
·Scale: Working with large data sets, where data sets don’t fit into memory, and require multiple nodes to compute efficiently.
·Machine Learning: A strong grasp of machine learning fundamentals (regularisation, over-fitting, hyperparameter optimisation, validation methods).
·Leadership skills: Experience with leading technical teams and mentoring.
 
Highly Desirable:
·Domain Knowledge – Statistics: Data mining and statistical analysis techniques 
·Cloud Computing: Experience with AWS or GCP.
·MLOps: Experience with operationalizing ML applications and workflows.
·Data: Experience with working with databases and preparing training and validation data.
·GIS: Knowledge of GIS tools and techniques.
 
Sound like you?
Then we’d love to chat with you about this and other Data Science opportunities
Either hit apply, or reach out to Greg Perl at The Onset on 0487848404 [link removed] or greg@theonset.com.au

teaser: Work at a rapidly expanding, caring and close-knit data science driven startup and give a voice to communities living near industrial developments!
desktopAdTemplate: Data ScientistAbout usVoconiq is a mission based, data driven startup providing a voice to communities living with proposed or existing industrial development. We have developed a sophisticated data analytic engine that translates community survey data into insight - we inform our customers’ thinking and actions with science.We work extensively in domains that are contested, where relationships between industry and community is strained, marked by conflict, and complex. Our customers are diverse, ranging from the world’s largest mining companies to government bodies and national agriculture bodies.The best news is we’re just getting started. We’re rapidly expanding our global presence and investing in technology to enable any person, anywhere in the world, the chance to have a voice inside the decision-making processes that affect them.What drives us every day is knowing we’re helping communities translate their experiences, concerns and aspirations into a language our customers can understand then use to maximise their positive impact.Just like the communities we serve, we’re a diverse team and on the hunt for people with fresh insight, new ways of working—and the same passion that we have—to make an impact on a local and global scale.About the roleWe’re looking for a data scientist with a background in the social or behavioral sciences to work closely alongside (and be mentored by) our superstar Chief Data Scientist, Dr Sean Murphy. The data science team has developed a world-leading data insights platform, and this role is an exciting opportunity to work within this team to build new tools and deepen analyses to make the insights we develop even more useful and impactful.You’ll be involved in designing surveys and experiments grounded in scientific literature, interviewing stakeholders, cleaning and collating data, conducting exploratory data analysis, building models, and generating and presenting insightful and compelling reports. You’ll be working in survey platforms like Qualtrics to collect data, in R to build robust data cleaning pipelines, and then using clean data to generate compelling dashboards, graphics, and statistical outputs to provide actionable insights for our clients. Who we’re looking forYou’re a capable problem solver who can readily demystify complex datasets to answer our client’s most difficult questions. You have an analytical mind and a genuine curiosity to better understand our customers and the industry they work in. You’re diligent, a stickler for detail, and are willing to learn and contribute to new R packages (including custom in-house tools) to maximise platform performance. Despite working closely alongside our Chief Data Scientist, you will be able to self-manage your priorities and delivery timetable.A deeper dive into what you’ll be doingInforming survey designs to ensure they answer key questions and address the needs of stakeholders.You’ll use, and help develop, inhouse R packages and the tidyverse to rapidly clean and verify the integrity of data, and generate descriptive graphics.Generating useful and timely reports, finding and highlighting key trends in data, supplementing these with high-level exploration of qualitative comments and feedback to create compelling, high-level summaries of “What’s going on” for our clients.Building interactive, visually appealing dashboards in R, shiny, JavaScript, html and CSS.You’ll work on continuous improvement, uncovering where possible useful information that isn’t currently being collected, or where survey questions aren’t tapping what they’re intended to.Helping to centralise our datasets into a central data warehouse and thinking about database structure and design.Promptly responding to ad-hoc analysis requests from our clients and their stakeholders.Essential skillsUndergraduate degree in a quantitative social science discipline or equivalent experienceStrong statistical skills (at least multiple regression, ideally structural equation modelling and mixed effects/multilevel modelling)Strong skills in the R language (tidyverse experience strongly desirable)Excellent communication skillsExperience with survey/research designExperience with Git / GithubDesirable skillsStrong stakeholder and expectation management skillsFamiliarity with R’s dashboarding tools such as shiny and flexdashboardR package development experienceJavascript and CSS experienceFamiliarity with cloud systems (e.g. Google Cloud)Database experience (e.g. SQL)Master’s degree or PhD in a quantitative social science disciplineInterested?The role is based in Melbourne, working in The Commons, a dynamic, warehouse-style coworking space full of small/startup companies (ad hoc work from home options are also available). You’ll be reporting into our Chief Data Scientist, Sean Murphy, and will receive strong mentoring in applying technical skills to industry data science problems, as well as training in advanced techniques. To learn more please contact Sean Murphy at sean.murphy@voconiq.com [link removed]. Applications close 4th June 2021. Submit your application, including a cover page, via the Seek Apply Now button, or by direct email to sean.murphy@voconiq.com [link removed].

teaser: Start your career as a Data Analyst/ Data Scientist Consultant. The Data School provides paid training and industry experience in Tableau and Alteryx.
desktopAdTemplate: Data is explodingThe demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of first-class data analysts and data scientists.If you are passionate about data, we have the best way to get you into your new data career.How does it work?The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx. In addition, you will be trained by our team of experts in all the soft skills needed to become an outstanding consultant.The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.Do I get paid to learn?Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.Key datesThe Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round is April, August and November.The applications for the August 2021 intake close on the 31st May, 2021 What’s in it for you  Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technologyBecome a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platformIt’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultantGain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in AustraliaLearn from the best data and analytics experts in AustraliaStudy in a creative work space in central SydneyDetails of the role    Four months of classroom trainingFour client engagements, each 6 months longThe result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second yearWe’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in AustraliaWhen you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to youWhat we’re looking for   Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience. What we are looking for is:Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every dayData-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomesTech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy itCuriosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and whyResourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re askingFast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this roleCreativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible formsApplication ProcessWe do things differently and we’re proud of it. So forget about the application process you might be used to.Here’s how the process works:Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us!The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the applicationWe are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!
