teaser: An opportunity to join a team developing an innovative national-scale ground surface movement product from satellite Earth Observation data.
desktopAdTemplate: Geoscience Australia is an Australian Government listed entity within the Industry, Science, Energy and Resources portfolio.   Geoscience Australia is Australia's pre-eminent public sector geoscience organisation. We are the nation's trusted advisor on the geology and geography of Australia. We apply science and technology to describe and understand the Earth for the benefit of Australia. We apply our diverse professional expertise, our deep and trusted knowledge, our national-scale Earth observation infrastructure and our strong partnerships, to the opportunities and challenges that face our nation.   We value diversity in gender, backgrounds, culture, and experiences of our employees and are committed to providing an inclusive workplace culture that ensures everyone has equal opportunity to contribute, participate and progress. Applications from people who reflect this diversity are encouraged.   We are committed to the health, safety and wellbeing of our employees and offer a flexible and diverse workplace.   As a Data Scientist you will apply your technical expertise in Interferometric Synthetic Aperture Radar (InSAR), high performance computing and/or big data processing to contribute to the development of a national-scale ground surface movement product that will support the strategic science priorities of Geoscience Australia and the broader Commonwealth Government.   Working under limited direction, in this role you will: Develop specialist software tools and technical applications to enable national-scale InSAR processing on high performance computing infrastructure and/or cloud environments Problem solve complex technical issues including the accurate interpretation of InSAR products and assembly of big data in to a single mosaicked product Conduct complex research and data analysis towards incrementally improving our products and understanding the physical contributions to measured InSAR signals Provide expert verbal and written advice and accurate interpretation of InSAR-derived products to internal and external stakeholders Promote the agency’s InSAR capability, and develop relationships with stakeholders leading to new agreements and collaborations Contribute to strategic planning for longer-term initiatives affecting GA’s InSAR capability Provide technical leadership, including professional supervision and reviewing the work of peers and staff at lower classification levels within the team Proactively develop own skills and technical knowledge in-line with strategic priorities of the InSAR team.

teaser: Drive Yello is searching for an experienced Data Scientist to join our Operations team.
desktopAdTemplate: Drive Yello helps businesses efficiently manage last-mile delivery and connects them to gig economy drivers, so they can meet the ever-increasing demand for convenience. We have ambitious growth plans and are looking for an inspiring Engineering Leader to drive the scaling of our application architecture and tech teams. We work with some of the largest retail clients here in Australia which include Woolworths, BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Coles, Terry White Chemmart just to name a few.The Yello Platform provides retailers unprecedented access to data and control of last-mile delivery and has proven to help businesses not only improve their delivery service but also enable them to provide delivery on demand. Retailers are attracted to Drive Yello as they not only get access to innovative technology but a marketplace of couriers to help them provide the convenience customers are demanding. About the role Drive Yello is searching for an experienced Data Scientist to join our Operations team. The Data Scientist will be responsible for our data & analytics projects and act as a link between tech and business. The role is a combination of both environments where you are going to scope, translate business requirements, support data warehouse development and have actual impact on our logistics platform. Main responsibilities Lead – from ideation to execution – several of Yello’s growth and performance improvement initiatives with direct revenue or cost impact Take ownership of the data science and analytics initiatives to strengthen our decision-making and effectivenessInteract with clients and platform users to gather business and system requirements Work across multiple functions with their respective teams, adopting a ‘multi-role’ style in problem-solving, developing sustainable solutions and functional specificationDevelop and maintain data warehouse, workflows, processes, reports in Google BigQuery and Microsoft PowerBI environments Prepare assets, models and dashboards to present findings, market and industry condition insightsImplement best practices of data modelling design in development and maintenance of databasesProvide senior management with regular business and project updates Consolidate and implement best practices across the business Support senior management with regular and ad hoc reports, business cases and other critical topics Required Skills/Experience Master degree in Engineering, Engineering Management, Business or similarYou gained at least 3-5 years and independent in handling business challenges You thrive in the challenge and are comfortable with ambiguity Compensation package Base salary range of $80k to $90k per annum plus superannuation.

teaser: Senior Data Engineering opportunity in a Financial Markets firm- Sydney CBD location, working in a high performing team building an AI driven platform
desktopAdTemplate: Our client is a financial markets focused high growth organisation with a revolutionary approach to portfolio, risk management and proprietary trading.They are leveraging technology and data science to enable high performance analytics in real time. Due to continued success and expansion we are looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join the team.This role will focus on:Learning the time series database and administering itEnsuring data is always available as neededWorking with dev team to create appropriate tables, data sets, queries, Quality assurance of data setsData mapping – this will be ongoing, and we would be seeking to automate the data mapping with machine learning over timeDesigning, deploying and maintaining SQL and potentially other DBs, tables, data sets, etc.Data structuring for ingestion by AI, ML, DL and other inference algorithms – also an ongoing exercise as data sets are addedTo be considered you must possess the following technical skills:DatabasesSignificant knowledge and experience of data base architecture, administration, integration, development and maintenance a mustOneTick time series database a strong advantageNoSQL an advantageDistributed data storage an advantageDataExperience working with large data sets Ability to develop rules for data QA and data cleaning and structuring prior to applying analyticsAbility to automate data QAWorking real time data sets that are dynamic Other Technical SkillsFull project lifecycle experience an advantageCritical systems experience a strong advantage i.e. environments that have high through-put with low-latency and minimal fault tolerance.Coding LanguagesFluency in SQL a must havePython a must havePearl Scripting, JSON and/or XML a strong advantageC++ a strong advantageTo be considered for this great opportunity please apply today.On offer is above market compensation, a great entrepreneurial and fast paced culture and the opportunity to work a top notch technical team.For candidates inclined to become Data Scientists this would be a career path to then grow into a Data Scientist role or have leadership prospects if that way inclined.Candidates must be available to work in the Sydney CBD office and have full working rights to work in Australia.

teaser: The Consumer Marketing team exists to build capability in consumer marketing people, processes and systems.
desktopAdTemplate:
Position Overview / Purpose:
Data Scientists apply scientific discovery processes, including hypothesis generation and hypothesis testing, to obtain actionable knowledge related to scientific problems and business processes, revealing any hidden relations between multiple processes.
This graduate data scientist is responsible for the research and the development of decision support systems for Consumer Marketing, with a specific focus on identifying opportunities to improve the generation and nurture of leads with the goal of growing the number of people choosing an implantable hearing solution from Cochlear.
Future projects may include the development of predictive models.
In addition to developing and improving advanced analytical techniques and algorithms, this person will be involved in the development of research data infrastructure and assist in the productisation of advanced algorithms.  This role will also involve training and supporting data analysis and engineering functions in performing basic analyses. The function is a global role based within the Consumer Marketing team (Global Marketing).
Accountabilities:
Accountability 1: Develop advanced algorithms to support Cochlear's vision
Collaborate on the development of algorithms to provide insights into the effectiveness of DTC marketing and consumer sales processes
Develop algorithms to detect and later predict the likelihood that a particular lead will progress to surgery and choose Cochlear.
Execute all research activities with high quality and efficiency
Collaborate closely with Consumer Marketing stakeholders and IT and BI colleagues.
Accountability 2: Collaborate on the development of data infrastructure
Support the Business Intelligence team with the development of cloud data stores for marketing and sales data
Develop data transformation pipelines and processing infrastructure for analysis of marketing and sales data.
Communicate Consumer Marketing data requirements to the Business Intelligence (cloud storage) team and engage in collaborative design to ensure these requirements are met.
Collaborate with data stewards, data architects and infrastructure architects to continue to evolve Cochlear's data infrastructure, quality and availability.
Accountability 3: Build marketing analytics and organisational data capability
Provide training and support to marketing analysts performing data analyses as part of their job.
Contribute to the development of organisational culture, processes and tools to support data driven decision making.
Continue to develop your own technical expertise and remain current on the latest developments in machine learning as they apply to your role.
Take an active role in developing novel approaches to business problems and understanding the customer and disseminate the knowledge gained this way to the Consumer Marketing group.
Seek opportunities to collaborate with other data scientist and analysts in Cochlear to solve common issues globally rather than repeatedly solving the same problem in every group
Key Incumbent requirements:
Minimum:
Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Physics or another technical field.
Fluent in Python, SQL
Highly comfortable with traditional supervised and unsupervised machine learning algorithms (e.g. decision trees, SVM, boosting, bagging, etc.)
Comfortable with version control systems, preferably git.
Comfortable with visualisations and storytelling methods to create dashboards and data analytics reports.
Highly comfortable in communicating the results of analyses in a clear and effective manner.
Comfortable with data processing models, data modelling and building data transformation pipelines.
Ability to work collaboratively in cross functional teams
Effective written and verbal communication skills
Ideal:
Masters degree in a data science related discipline
Experience with text data mining, marketing & customer analytics, natural language processing and information extraction
Experience with big data cloud technologies, preferably on the AWS or Google stack
Knowledgeable in consumer marketing and digital marketing
Development Value of this role:
Become the company wide expert and research lead on artificial intelligence techniques for marketing
Master structured research and innovation processes in a medical device company and gain in autonomy and competence
Work with a global team of researchers in audiology, sound processing and clinical care
Build experience with big data problems relevant to marketing in the hearing industry
Region-specific Requirements:
Frequent interaction with analysts around the world.

teaser: The Australian Bureau of Statistics is looking to fill multiple Statisticians and Data Professional roles (APS 4) in our Methodology Division.
desktopAdTemplate: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to fill multiple Statisticians and Data Professional roles (APS 4) in our Methodology Division (MD).The roles are permanent positions, available as full-time or part-time, to be filled in the Canberra, Sydney, Melbourne, Geelong, Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide ABS offices.About the RoleWe are seeking motivated people with skills in fields such as statistics, data science, mathematics, modelling and analysis, survey sampling and estimation, questionnaire design and evaluation, statistical disclosure control, statistical data integration, economics / econometrics or time series analysis. The roles are best suited to people who work well in a team environment, have strong problem-solving skills, and are able to work flexibly to agreed priorities and deadlines.A career in MD will provide opportunities to develop expertise in methods used in the conduct of official statistics, and opportunities to develop and adapt new methods to be used in the ABS in the future. Successful applicants will have future opportunities to be transferred or promoted within MD or move to other interesting roles across the ABS.The positions offer flexible working arrangements (in terms of hours and/or doing some work from home), working in virtual teams (across the country) and collaborating with external methodologists and other experts in academia, other government agencies or overseas in other National Statistical Offices.As an APS4 in the Methodology Division you will: working under supervision, contribute to methodological projects and provide methodological support to other parts of the ABS take initiative and manage your own work outputs while working independently or as part of a team present the results of methodological work to internal and external audiences in meetings or seminars conduct and prepare reports on research projects and empirical studies.For Mathematical Statistician/Data Scientist roles, you will use statistical computing languages (for example R, Python or SAS) to manipulate data for statistical design and/or analysis.What we are looking forTo be suitable you should have most of or all the skills, qualities and experience outlined in Section 4 of the Applicant Information Kit attached.Tertiary qualifications in data science, statistics, mathematics, physics, computer science, econometrics/economics, bioinformatics, psychology, or another field with a strong quantitative component are highly desirable, with qualifications at honours level or above being a further advantage. A demonstrated ability to learn and apply new methods and technologies will also be highly regarded.How to ApplyFor further information on eligibility for the role and what qualities, experiences and skills we are looking for, please ensure you read through the Applicant Information Kit.Applications close at 11:30PM AEST on Wednesday 9 June 2021.

desktopAdTemplate: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to fill multiple Statisticians and Data Professional roles (APS 4) in our Methodology Division (MD).The roles are permanent positions, available as full-time or part-time, to be filled in the Canberra, Sydney, Melbourne, Geelong, Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide ABS offices.About the RoleWe are seeking motivated people with skills in fields such as statistics, data science, mathematics, modelling and analysis, survey sampling and estimation, questionnaire design and evaluation, statistical disclosure control, statistical data integration, economics / econometrics or time series analysis. The roles are best suited to people who work well in a team environment, have strong problem-solving skills, and are able to work flexibly to agreed priorities and deadlines.A career in MD will provide opportunities to develop expertise in methods used in the conduct of official statistics, and opportunities to develop and adapt new methods to be used in the ABS in the future. Successful applicants will have future opportunities to be transferred or promoted within MD or move to other interesting roles across the ABS.The positions offer flexible working arrangements (in terms of hours and/or doing some work from home), working in virtual teams (across the country) and collaborating with external methodologists and other experts in academia, other government agencies or overseas in other National Statistical Offices.As an APS4 in the Methodology Division you will: working under supervision, contribute to methodological projects and provide methodological support to other parts of the ABS take initiative and manage your own work outputs while working independently or as part of a team present the results of methodological work to internal and external audiences in meetings or seminars conduct and prepare reports on research projects and empirical studies.For Mathematical Statistician/Data Scientist roles, you will use statistical computing languages (for example R, Python or SAS) to manipulate data for statistical design and/or analysis.What we are looking forTo be suitable you should have most of or all the skills, qualities and experience outlined in Section 4 of the Applicant Information Kit attached.Tertiary qualifications in data science, statistics, mathematics, physics, computer science, econometrics/economics, bioinformatics, psychology, or another field with a strong quantitative component are highly desirable, with qualifications at honours level or above being a further advantage. A demonstrated ability to learn and apply new methods and technologies will also be highly regarded.How to ApplyFor further information on eligibility for the role and what qualities, experiences and skills we are looking for, please ensure you read through the Applicant Information Kit.Applications close at 11:30PM AEST on Wednesday 9 June 2021.

teaser: Opportunity to build a career with a successful startup & work with some of the best companies in AU | Top Comm Structure with HUGE earning potential!
desktopAdTemplate: TheDriveGroup: Driven by Technology, Powered by People.    We are a young and ambitious specialist technology solutions consultancy, focused on mutual partnerships and long-term relationships.    Due to high demand, we are expanding the business and growing our teams in Sydney & Melbourne!    We have multiple openings for:Resourcers Recruitment Consultants Senior Consultants Principal Consultants   Team Leaders  Any previous experience across areas/desks such as Product, UI/UX Design, Software Engineering (.NET, Java, PHP, RoR, Golang, Python etc), Front End / JavaScript, Data/BI, Cyber, Infrastructure, Salesforce or similar will be highly regarded!The Role/Our Company:    This is a rare opportunity for someone to get in early and join a successful scaling company whilst we are still young and you can really carve out your own career and path!    What does that mean exactly?    It means:TOP Commission Structure (Up To 50%) / Annual Bonus / HUGE Earning potential! Flat structure / No bulls**t / no office dramas! 100% collaboration / Work with other high performers on the same mission Defined career path / Work towards Team Lead, Manager & Director Perform & work your own hours / work from home Casual Fridays every day! Shorts, T-shirts, Jeans, Tuxedo - it's up to you! Cool Surry Hills offices surrounded by the best bars, pubs & cafes in Sydney Pet-friendly office - bring your dog to work! Choose your own equipment - Stand Up Desks, New Apple Mac, curved screens, wireless headsets etc Never-ending drinks fridge - Redbull, beer, wine etc Extra paid days off including your Birthday Monthly Lunch Club, Quarterly Individual and Team Targets Annual competition/team trip! (eg Skiing or Las Vegas) And our favourite - unlimited Holiday!!  With a combination of high commission and company incentives, there is never a dull day. Worried about what area you will work in - don't worry. We have not broken down the market into small areas where you will be limited to a small market/desk - you will be given a good chunk of the pie, able to work across multiple markets and dual desk if you wish.    Oh ye, we also have NO KPI's. So don't worry about someone watching over your shoulder checking on your calls and how many interviews you have locked in for the week. Everyone runs their own business here and we all work as a team on the same mission!   About You / what we are looking for:    You should be comfortable in an "all hands on deck" environment, love solving problems, you can juggle 10 tasks at once, you can thrive in a startup culture - but most of all - you genuinely enjoy helping others and want to change lives!    And you should also have experience working in a recruitment-focused role and ideally in the Technology sector.    Simple as that!    We hire people who are determined and we favour ability over experience.    Unrivalled ambition and razor-sharp focus are what makes our service so distinctive and our consultants all share one distinguishing quality which is - Drive!    We are driven by delivery, success and focus on engaging in long-term relationships, not just transactions.    Our team also like to stay pretty fit and active, attend the gym/workout and take part in events such as Spartan and City2Surf - but we also like to eat out, drink, and have fun :)    If you like the sound of what we do, how we work and think you would fit in well here - let's chat! How to apply / next steps:Shoot through a resume or the link to your Linkedin profile A cover letter is optional but would help us get to know you Australian Citizenship, Permanent Residency or eligibility to work full-time in Australia is required (Visa transfers available for the right person). Nobody likes "interviews" so if you look like you have what it takes then we will give you a call or grab a coffee. If you haven't moved companies or updated your resume for a while, feel free to just drop us an email and tell us a bit about yourself instead. Contact James on: jsullivan@thedrivegroup.com.au Unfortunately, due to the high amount of applications we receive, we can only contact successful applicants. We look forward to hearing from you :)       Some of the areas/roles we have successfully recruited for recently: Front End Developer, Java Developer, .Net Developer, JavaScript Developer, NodeJS Developer, MEAN Stack Developer, MERN Stack Developer, Full Stack JavaScript Developer, iOS Developer, Android Developer, PHP Developer, UX Developer, UX/UI Designer, Product Manager, Ruby on Rails, Python, Golang Engineer, Scala Engineer, HTML5, CSS3, Angular, React, Vue, Business Analyst, Test Analyst, QA Engineer, Project Manager, Scrum Master, Agile Coach, CTO, Development Manager, IT Manager, Tech Director, Head of Engineering, Head of Technology, DevOps, Data Scientist, Technical Lead, Cloud & Solution Architect.

teaser: Advance your unstoppable career at the University of South Australia with a research degree. Become an expert and make a difference to society.
desktopAdTemplate: The University of South Australia (UniSA) is Australia’s University of Enterprise. We are South Australia’s largest university and one of the very best young universities in the world. At UniSA, we are authentic, resilient, and influential - and we deliver results. We pride ourselves on our dynamic and agile culture, which embraces challenges and thrives on breaking new ground. Plus, we are committed to the principles of excellence and equity. Our people are critical to our success. They are creative, enterprising and innovative thinkers, communicating with clarity, conviction and enthusiasm. We educate global professionals ready to create and inspire change, through more than 200 world-class degrees. We deliver outcomes-focused research that is inspired by global challenges and opportunities, to deliver economic and social prosperity. Our strategic plan, Enterprise25, focusses on our people, programs and precincts, and sets out our path to ensure that we continue to deliver quality teaching, research and student outcomes. 100% of our assessed research rated at or above world-class - 2018 Excellence in Research for Australia (ERA), 4-digit Fields of Research. No. 1 in Australia for industry research income - 2019 THE World University Rankings. No. 1 in Australia for research impact & engagement - 2018 ARC Engagement and Impact Assessment (EI), Combined Impact – Approach to Impact and Engagement on Assessed Fields. Athena Swan Bronze Award.About the research degree project Undertake a project at UniSA’s Quality Use of Medicine and Pharmacy Research Centre with research that aligns with a National Health and Medical Research Council (NHMRC) project grant “Large scale evidence generation for the utilisation and safety of biologic medicines”. This pharmacovigilance project will focus on the use of biologic medicines to treat autoimmune diseases such as inflammatory bowel diseases Crohn’s disease and/or ulcerative colitis. With a primary focus on the safety of biologic treatments, you will look at the utilisation and treatment patterns of these medicines before establishing known risks in spontaneous adverse drug event databases such as the FDA Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS). Once known risks are quantified and used as baseline true positive signals, you will find unknown signals concerning medicine safety to be further studied in a predictive framework on prospective cohort data.This project is suitable for either a pharmacist who is interested in developing their data analysis skills or a quantitative scientist (statistician or data scientist) who has an interest in biological applications of their skills. You will collaborate with pharmacists, epidemiologists, statisticians and computer scientists to develop highly relevant skills in pharmacovigilance and related biological and data sciences, as well as undertake important research that aims to benefit patients around the world.The NHMRC grant this project aligns to seeks to: utilise global research data networks to monitor the safety of biologics; profile trends and treatment patterns of biologics globally and investigate how these treatment patterns contribute to harm; and generate evidence on the risks and extent of harm of biologics in real world practice.Supervisory team Associate Professor Nicole Pratt (Principal Supervisor) Dr Ty Stanford Dr Jodie Hillen Dr Ben Daniels (University of NSW)Eligibility and selectionThis project is open to applications from Australian or New Zealand citizens, and Australian permanent residents or permanent humanitarian visa holders. International applicants are not invited to apply at this time.Applicants must meet the eligibility criteria for entrance into a PhD at UniSA. Additionally, applicants who are able to demonstrate their knowledge in the following areas will be highly regarded: An undergraduate degree in a healthcare-related discipline or biostatistics, with an understanding of quality use of medicines issues. Highly proficient in software applications such as Word, Excel and PowerPoint. Skills in analytical software packages such as SPSS, R or STATA. Completion of an Honours project or master’s (by research or coursework) qualification. Good written and verbal communication skills combined with demonstrated ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.The successful applicant is expected to study full-time and be based at our City East campus in the heart of Adelaide.Financial supportThis project is funded for reasonable research expenses. Additionally, a living allowance scholarship of $28,597 per annum is available to Australian and New Zealand citizens, and permanent residents of Australia, including permanent humanitarian visa holders. A fee-offset or waiver for the standard term of the program is also included. For full terms and benefits of the scholarship please refer to our  scholarship information.An additional top-up scholarship with a value of $6,000 per annum will be offered to the successful applicant commensurate with experience (such as clinical knowledge and previous publications in discipline).How to apply Applications must be lodged online, please note UniSA does not accept applications via email. For further support see our step-by-step guide on how to apply , contact the Graduate Research team on +61 8 8302 5880, or email us at research.admissions@unisa.edu.au. Enquiries will receive a response within one working day. Applications will remain open until 11:30pm ACST Wednesday 16 June 2021.  You are encouraged to apply early. Please note: The successful applicant is expected to start shortly after receiving their offer. Extended deferral periods are not available.

teaser: Reporting to the Strategic Projects Manager, the role of the Commercial Data and Insights Analyst works closely with a multitude of Delivery Hub team
desktopAdTemplate: Bupa is a leading health insurance provider in Australia. Our customers include over 4.7 million Australian residents as well as international visitors who come to Australia as a tourist, worker or students.Reporting to the Strategic Projects Manager, the role of the Commercial Data and Insights Analyst works closely with a multitude of Delivery Hub team members to resolve the most impactful customer and commercial, multi-variant problems.With experience in Private Health Insurance, large change programs and agile ways of working, the role will be critical for scientifically determining the most salient drivers of customer and commercial performance to improve decision-making across our Health Insurance agile squads, planned delivery teams and Accelerated Performance and Delivery team. What do I need? Tertiary qualification in data science, statistics, mathematics, computer science, machine learning, applied statistics or mathematicsAt least two years' experience - as an analyst or data scientist - working on customer and commercial transformation programsFluency in at least one of the following programming languages SAS, R, Python and Scala.Proficient in advanced analytics tools, including R, Excel and VBA, SAS, GA360, Big Query, Tableau and datasets such as Google Analytics and Adobe Analytics Experience with technologies like AWS EMR to support ETL processing on large data sources or with computationally intensive steps (SQL, parallelization, Hadoop, Spark, etc.) What is it like to work there? Be at the heart of helping people live longer, healthier, happier lives. At Bupa, we employ more than 80,000 people globally who are making this a reality. One thing stands out about Bupa people -our customers are our passion; they're at the heart of our culture of care. If you've got the belief, the drive and the talent to help us in our ambition then we'd like to hear from you.

teaser: A permanent full-time opportunity for a data scientist to join the Remote Sensing Centre providing expertise to protect and manage our environment.
desktopAdTemplate:
As a Senior Scientist in the Remote Sensing Centre, you will provide scientific and technical leadership in a team of remote sensing scientists who develop and deliver high quality scientific information and advice to support government programs and policy, including Great Barrier Reef protection.
You will be mentoring, energising and influencing a small team of remote sensing scientists and collaborating with internal and external partners to deliver high quality, scientifically defensible products, that includes quantitative and statistical analysis and visualisation of data and results. This will involve developing innovative solutions to deliver mapping and monitoring of land cover, particularly ground cover and fire. 
Your skills in data management, data publishing and web-based data delivery applications will be utilised across the Centre and you will be required to communicate and translate complex scientific information to a range of audiences using a variety of media.
Who will thrive in this role:
A person with a strong data science background who is:
• Able to apply new approaches to working with data to solve problems and deliver it in innovative and informative ways
• Able to lead, mentor and motivate
• Open to new ways of thinking and adaptable to change
• Motivated by contributing to a positive environmental legacy for future generations
What we are looking for -
We'll assess your merit for this role by looking at what you've done previously - the knowledge, skills and experience you've built, your potential for development, and your personal qualities.
Please refer to the attached position description which further outlines “Your role” and “What we are looking for”.
How to apply:
To enable us to assess your merit, you should:
• apply online at www.smartjobs.qld.gov.au
• include your current resume (of no more than six pages) with two referees including your current supervisor.
• provide a short statement (of no more than two pages) explaining why you are interested in the role.
Applications to remain current for 12 months
 
Job Ad Reference: QLD/375878/21
 
Closing Date: Wednesday 23 June 2021

Your skills in data management, data publishing and web-based data delivery applications will be utilised across the Centre and you will be required to communicate and translate complex scientific information to a range of audiences using a variety of media.
Who will thrive in this role:
A person with a strong data science background who is:
• Able to apply new approaches to working with data to solve problems and deliver it in innovative and informative ways
• Able to lead, mentor and motivate
• Open to new ways of thinking and adaptable to change
• Motivated by contributing to a positive environmental legacy for future generations
What we are looking for -
We'll assess your merit for this role by looking at what you've done previously - the knowledge, skills and experience you've built, your potential for development, and your personal qualities.
Please refer to the attached position description which further outlines “Your role” and “What we are looking for”.
How to apply:
To enable us to assess your merit, you should:
• apply online at www.smartjobs.qld.gov.au
• include your current resume (of no more than six pages) with two referees including your current supervisor.
• provide a short statement (of no more than two pages) explaining why you are interested in the role.
Applications to remain current for 12 months

Nobody likes "interviews" so if you look like you have what it takes then we will give you a call or grab a coffee. If you haven't moved companies or updated your resume for a while, feel free to just drop us an email and tell us a bit about yourself instead. Contact James on: jsullivan@thedrivegroup.com.au Unfortunately, due to the high amount of applications we receive, we can only contact successful applicants. We look forward to hearing from you :)       Some of the areas/roles we have successfully recruited for recently: Front End Developer, Java Developer, .Net Developer, JavaScript Developer, NodeJS Developer, MEAN Stack Developer, MERN Stack Developer, Full Stack JavaScript Developer, iOS Developer, Android Developer, PHP Developer, UX Developer, UX/UI Designer, Product Manager, Ruby on Rails, Python, Golang Engineer, Scala Engineer, HTML5, CSS3, Angular, React, Vue, Business Analyst, Test Analyst, QA Engineer, Project Manager, Scrum Master, Agile Coach, CTO, Development Manager, IT Manager, Tech Director, Head of Engineering, Head of Technology, DevOps, Data Scientist, Technical Lead, Cloud & Solution Architect.

desktopAdTemplate: The Position:Would you like to use data science to solve real world problems whilst continually learning and developing your skills within a diverse, supportive team environment?You could be joining an industry leading financial business in Sydney. Data Scientists tackle the full product life cycle from an idea through to a productionised model; this gives a great sense of ownership over the data products we build. Think fast-paced environment where they balance “having something now" vs. "perfection in the future"Your Responsibilities:Strategic Mind-set: takes a long-term view and anticipates future trends and implicationsBusiness Insights: has a nose for business, uses insights to impact commercial driversCollaborates: is a team player - works with others across the organisation to get things doneCustomer focus: Thinks about customers 24/7, and puts them at the heart of all that we doPartner with internal stakeholders on projects to identify and articulate opportunities, see beyond the data to identify solutions that will raise the bar for decision making. Your Background:Degree in a quantitative field such as Computer Science, Quantitative Finance, Math, Statistics, Physics degree.Experience with Advanced Analytics, Statistics, or other data analysis tools and techniques.Experience with statistics methods such as forecasting, time series, hypothesis testing, classification, clustering or regression analysis.You have strong technical skills in data manipulation and extraction (strong SQL knowledge), data analysis and model prototyping and productionisation (Python, R or similar)Knowledge of cloud data environments e.g., AWS would be ideal but not requiredCommercial experience of deep-dive analysis of complex data; managing data quality; feature selection; and prototyping, validation, and productionisation of Machine Learning models.3+ years of related industry experience in the data science domain This is a fantastic opportunity paying above market rates and working with a reputable global brand. If this isn’t quite the role for you but you have experience working as a data science and looking for your next opportunity, get in touch.For further information on this role or to confidentially apply, please contact Raj Sharif on 02 8227 9200 or apply directly via the Apply for this job button. teaser: The School of Veterinary Science is seeking a Data Scientist to support building & utilising OHSARK's digital research platforms at the Gatton Campus.
desktopAdTemplate:
­­­School of Veterinary Science
Founded in 1936, the School of Veterinary Science has a rich history and a reputation for graduating self-reliant, independent and highly capable veterinarians with plenty of initiative and drive. The School has high quality facilities at the UQ Gatton Campus, providing the teaching, research and clinical infrastructure and resources to develop its strong reputation as a leading provider of veterinary training, research and clinical care. The school also maintains a Small Animal Hospital and Large Animal Clinic at Dayboro, north-west of Brisbane.
UQ SpatialEpiLab
The UQ SpatialEpiLab is a One Health medical geography research group based at the School of Veterinary Science established in 2015. The UQ SpatiaEpiLab currently houses +20 staff and research students with a focus on big-data and spatial infectious disease and animal cancer surveillance projects. With a diversity of backgrounds and perspectives, the staff and students at the UQ SpatialEpiLab have broad expertise in health sciences, mathematical modelling, social sciences, ecology and epidemiology. With the support of federal and industry-led projects the UQ Spatial Epidemiology Laboratory is establishing the One Health Surveillance and Analytics Research Unit (OHSARK unit) to conduct research at the interface between animal and human public health. We work with a range of international partners to blend our multidisciplinary expertise and deliver in-depth investigations for many important pathogens around the world. Information about the UQ Spatial Epidemiology Laboratory may be accessed at http://www.spatialepilab.com.
About This Opportunity
OHSARK is building a cloud-native software and platforms to streamline data processing and analysis of human and animal disease data. This is a great opportunity for an experienced Data Scientist to provide support for building and utilising OHSARK’s resulting digital research platforms by supporting the generation of the underlying analysis pipelines. In the role, you will work to engineer raw data into analysis-ready format and deploy statistical and machine learning models in the cloud to support epidemiological visualisations and investigations. This exciting opportunity will have you working alongside the Business Analyst, Senior Software Engineer, and domain scientists across partner institutes and collaboratively funded projects.
For a full list of duties and responsibilities, please refer to the Position Description below.
This position is located at The University of Queensland’s picturesque Gatton Campus. Gatton Campus, UQ combines its Queensland Agricultural College heritage with modern research and teaching facilities in agriculture, agribusiness and veterinary science. Just over an hour’s drive west of Brisbane and five kilometres from the local township, the 1068-hectare Gatton campus offers a relaxed, friendly atmosphere and world-class facilities including the Queensland Animal Science Precinct, the UQ Veterinary Medical Centre, Gatton Research Dairy, nursery and glasshouse facilities, the southern hemisphere’s largest PV solar array research facility, and a pesticide wind tunnel facility. The campus also operates several commercial plant and animal production units in rural technologies to support teaching, research and hands-on training.
Our Ideal Candidate
Applicants must have a degree qualification in a relevant discipline such as health, ecology, statistics, or epidemiology. You will demonstrate strong quantitative reasoning, problem solving and analytical skills, with experience with time-series analysis and/or spatial analysis models. You will have demonstrated research-level data analysis and unit testing experience using C++, Python and/or R. Experience in software version control such as GIT will also set you up for success in this role. Our ideal candidate will also have excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work under pressure and meet deadlines.
Experience developing data visualization dashboards and deploying multi-core models on high performance computing clusters is highly regarded, but not essential.
You must have ongoing unrestricted work rights in Australia to apply for this opportunity.
The University of Queensland values diversity and inclusion and actively encourages applications from those who bring diversity to the University. Please refer to the University’s Diversity and Inclusion webpage (https://staff.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/human-resources/diversity) for further information and points of contact if you require additional support.  Accessibility requirements and/or adjustments can be directed to the contact person listed in the job advertisement.
What We Can Offer
This is a full-time, fixed term position until December 2023 at HEW Level 5.
The remuneration will be in the range of $70,796.58 - $78,852.96, plus employer superannuation of 17%. The total FTE package will be in the range of $82,831.99 - $92.257.96.
You will be able to take advantage of UQ Sport Facilities, salary sacrificing options, on-campus childcare, discounted private health insurance, free parking, discounted veterinary access, development programs and many other benefits.
For further information, please review The University of Queensland's Enterprise Bargaining Agreement 2018-2021

Questions?
To discuss this role, please contact Dr Nicholas Clark.

To submit an application for this role, use the Apply button below. All applicants must supply the following documents:
Cover letter addressing selection criteria
Resume 
Applications Close: 13 July 2021 at 11:00pm AEST.

teaser: Data Engineer / Analyst in ML/AI Team with 3-5+ years experience, to build scalable Data Lakes, ELT/ETL systems, & analytics reporting.
desktopAdTemplate: Position Summary  Safesite ML & AI Team is hiring one of our earliest Data Engineers to build pipelines and maintain Data Lakes and Feature Stores for ML. The primary focus will be in handling the design and development of scalable ELT/ETL systems, analytics reporting, implementing testing and validation to ensure that data systems meet company requirements while being a good team player.  About Safesite  Safesite is one of the world's fastest growing digital risk management systems with over 3,000 companies using our technology worldwide.  As an employee of Safesite, you will be making a measurable impact on people's lives by reducing injuries and deaths in the workplace with every commit you make.  By capturing critical safety and risk data from the frontline workers in high-risk class codes, Safesite is able to accurately predict and help customers prevent workplace injuries. 4,000 US companies use the Safesite app and desktop portal on a daily basis to facilitate OSHA compliance activities, drive safety engagement, and dramatically reduce incidents and claim frequency. Safesite brings an advanced digital solution to the traditional loss control model.   Check out our website here https://safesitehq.com/about-safesite/.  What you'll do in this role:  Reporting to the Lead Data Scientist, the Data Engineer/Analyst will support the data engineering and analytics reporting services for Safesite to contribute to improving the delivery of quality services, and have a unique opportunity to shape and create our best methods in data analysis and reporting. All of this while working with an incredibly rich dataset enabling countless possibilities to effect real change in people's lives.  The work you do here has the ability to save lives. Understand and implement data engineering best practices Design, construct, install, test and maintain data engineering systems Develop set processes for data modelling, and data production Testing and validating data to ensure that they are fit for use Preparing raw data for manipulation by Data Scientists Recommend different ways to constantly improve data reliability and quality Ship medium to large features independently Generate architecture recommendations and the ability to implement them Analytics and visualisation of various experiments in the form of Data journalism. Great communication: Regularly achieve consensus amongst teamsWe're looking for: 3-5 years minimum, hands-on experience deploying production quality code Professional experience using Python or Spark for data processing (Python preferred) Knowledge of and experience with data-related packages & frameworks Demonstrably deep understanding of SQL and analytical data warehouses Hands-on experience implementing ETL (or ELT) best practices at scale. Hands-on experience with data pipeline tools (Airflow, Dagster, Argo, dbt, etc) Proven experience as a Data Engineer, Software Developer, or similar Technical expertise with Kubernetes, docker, dataOps/devOps and pipelining Excellent understanding of SQL databases like PostgreSQL, etc Experience using: AWS stack.Perks & Packages Competitive salary Equity in a high-growth company Flexible vacation Monthly wellness stipend Learning and Development stipendsSafesite offers an incredibly unique work environment. The company employs a diverse and talented team all over the world. Each Safesite team member is given the freedom and tools to do their best work from wherever they choose.  We are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, colour, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know.

teaser: Start your career as a Data Analyst/ Data Scientist Consultant. The Data School provides paid training and industry experience in Tableau and Alteryx.
desktopAdTemplate: Data is explodingThe demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of first-class data analysts and data scientists.If you are passionate about data, we have the best way to get you into your new data career.How does it work?The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx. In addition, you will be trained by our team of experts in all the soft skills needed to become an outstanding consultant.The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.Do I get paid to learn?Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.Key datesThe Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round in Sydney are April, August and November.The applications for the November 2021 intake close on the 27th of September, 2021 What’s in it for you  Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technologyBecome a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platformIt’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultantGain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in AustraliaLearn from the best data and analytics experts in AustraliaStudy in a creative work space in central SydneyDetails of the role    Four months of classroom trainingFour client engagements, each 6 months longThe result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second yearWe’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in AustraliaWhen you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to youWhat we’re looking for   Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience. What we are looking for is:Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every dayData-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomesTech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy itCuriosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and whyResourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re askingFast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this roleCreativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible formsApplication ProcessWe do things differently and we’re proud of it. So forget about the application process you might be used to.Here’s how the process works:Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us!The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the applicationWe are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

teaser: The Australian Signals Directorate is seeking to fill a number of ASD4-6 positions within the agency.
desktopAdTemplate: Do you like to grapple with complex and unusual problems? Can you be counted on to find innovative and clever solutions? Are you interested in doing things most people cannot?ASD are looking for tech savvy people from all backgrounds, with ranging levels of experience, to help us operate some of the most powerful, leading-edge technologies in a dynamic environment to support our objectives. The work we do is unique, critical and incredibly rewarding. We are looking for applicants with the ability to think critically, who are able to communicate with both technical and non-technical people, and who are motivated to learn and develop their skills.Ideal candidates will be innovative, team orientated and have a passion for building or supporting strategically important ASD capability.Regardless of the role, we want people who are able to work within a team environment and use their curiosity, resilience and creativity to solve problems involved in out-thinking and out-imagining some of the most testing adversaries.We are looking for people who can work under general direction to perform and achieve moderately complex technical activities relating to signals intelligence mission objectives.  The ideal candidate will exercise good judgement, demonstrate initiative and have a focus on continuous improvement.You will have the opportunity to deliver technical and operational support across the organisation in roles such as: ICT Business AnalystICT Enterprise ArchitectICT Project ManagerICT Security Specialist / ICT Information Security SpecialistsICT Solutions ArchitectICT Engineer ProfessionalICT Network Engineer / Network Test EngineerICT Systems Administrator / ICT Systems ArchitectICT Vendor Manager / Contract ManagerVoice and Video Specialist / Audio Visual SpecialistICT Customer Support OfficersICT Multimedia SpecialistICT Support EngineerICT Web Administrator / ICT Web DeveloperPrinting OfficerData Scientist / Data Analyst / Data Engineer ASD continues to grow and is always looking for talented people to join its mission. The following are examples of some of the work you could apply your technical expertise to: IT Systems Communications: digital and analogue, fixed and mobile wireless, satellite, antenna designEngineer and maintain international communication networks Design and program software solutions using a variety of programming languages such as C/C++, Java or Python to solve unique problems Microelectronics: VHDL, FPGA, microelectronic manufacturing and testing (MCM, SOC) electronic packaging, VLSI Network engineering: design and analysis of LANs/WANs, routers, switches, firewalls, protocols Perform testing, systems integrations and deploy mission-critical systemsSystems engineering:  end-to-end real-time operating systems, signals processing, VHDL/hardware development.Build and run high-performance super-computersDesign and implement container based application solutions using Docker and Kubernetes based platform servicesCommunicate closely with customers and provide expertise to support complex and critical projects Carry out computer forensics Collect and exploit target communications Network design and risk management Offensive cyber operations Respond to incidents on critical networks Reverse engineering Vulnerability analysis Software Development & EngineeringSoftware engineering: Java, C++, Perl, Python, Ruby, PowerShell, XML, HTML, web applications, object-oriented analysis and design, rapid prototyping, algorithm development PHP, Python, JavaScript frameworks, user interface development, open source plugin/module developmentCloud/container infrastructure design for high-availability enterprise information applications, including continuous deployment from Git managed code in OpenStack, AWS and Azure environments. Working knowledge of Containers/Kubernetes deployments.Multimedia & Publishing ServicesAudio Visual Specialists scoping, designing, installing, and testing complex audio visual systems across the organisation and across the country.Graphic Design Specialists liaising with stakeholders from across the organisation to provide high-level graphic design services using Adobe Design Suite software.Multimedia Specialists using editing and publication development software to develop audio and visual productions and to assist with the development of multimedia learning presentations across ASD. Content Developers and Editors providing high-quality structural editing, copyediting and proofreading to ensure ASD’s written communications are professionally presented, can be clearly interpreted, are accurate, grammatically correct, and comply with accessibility legislative requirements. ICT Word Template Development Specialists creating and maintaining corporate Word templates using VBA and XML coding in compliance with ASD and Commonwealth documentation and branding standards, while maintaining visual consistency and functionality across ASD’s corporate documents.Printing Officers using complex and computer-driven, industrial-scale printers and associated equipment to conduct publishing, printing and reprographic tasks and activities in accordance with ASD standards.Web design and web content authoring, editing, publishing and review as well as web service life-cycle management.ICT Customer Support OfficersLiaise with a diverse range of personnel across the Intelligence Community to provide support, respond to customer requests and provide timely advice and information.Use application management software and tools to manage ICT requests and incidents.Identify automation that improves the end user experience.Provide 1st level incident response, identify workarounds and resolve problems.Analyse data, assess business workflows and procedures and communicate recommendations to management for process improvement.Manage team roles and activities for service management processes and functions.Data Science, Analytics & Engineering Develop new and innovative data analytics.Provide support for security operations functions and database technologies such as SQL, Maria DB and PostgreQSL.Determine questions that need to be answered by developing hypotheses, gathering, organising and cleaning raw data.Apply algorithms in order to explore, analyse and interpret patterns in the data.Create data-driven solutions for identified problems and issues, and communicate the results to a wide variety of personnel and stakeholders.Information Security Computer and network securityCryptographic services Incident response Penetration testing Vulnerability analysis 895IT security threat assessments, policy and advice System ArchitectsAssess the integrity and integration of information from all available sources through the application of a variety of analytical and presentation techniques.Assess operational requirements, problems and opportunities, seeking effective business solutions through improvements in new or changed processes.Evaluate and appraise architectures based on evidence and assessments to ensure compliance with agreed procedures.Develop models and plans to implement or influence strategy to improve business performance. Develop and maintain architectural artefacts to support mission objectives.Identify and assess the relevance and risk of new and emerging hardware and software technologies and products to support ASD’s ICT strategies.Systems AdministratorsDesign, manage, integrate and ensure system integrity and performance tuning and monitoring across data processing, collaboration and communication applications including Splunk, ELK, Microsoft SCSM, SharePoint and the Atlassian suite.Perform routing installation, patching, upgrading and uninstallation of operating systems and application software.Contribute to the design, development, testing, implementation, documentation, support, security, maintenance or enhancement of ASD's communication and processing systems.Use experience in change management to maintain the continuity of capability delivered by IT operations and business functions.Provide Automated Configuration Management activities using Puppet, Salt, Ansible Azure Devops, Kubenetes and/or container management tools. Design, manage and integrate desktop physical and virtual systems.Design, deploy and support Windows desktop solutions on physical, and, virtual VMWare and Citrix platforms.Solve issues for unpredictable problems and establish operating policies, procedures and documentation.ASD continues to grow and is continually looking for talented people to join our mission.This will be a rolling-recruitment process, which means it will be conducted regularly. If you are successful in the application and assessment process you will be placed in a merit pool and may be contacted for further testing as positions become available. These may be ongoing or non-ongoing opportunities.Throughout the year, ASD may contact you to reconfirm your interest in roles and update you with any relevant information. We request that you also let us know if your circumstances change and you no longer wish to remain in the merit pool.Qualifications / Experience RequirementsASD is looking for qualified and/or experienced IT technologists. University qualifications are desirable but not essential.Eligibility Please ensure that you meet the eligibility requirements outlined in this Information Pack before submitting an application.Citizenship - To be eligible for employment with ASD, applicants must be an Australian citizen.  Health Assessment - The preferred applicants may be required to undergo a medical examination conducted by the Agency’s preferred medical provider. Organisational Assessment – To be eligible for employment within ASD, the preferred applicants will be required to undergo an Organisational Assessment (see Organisational Assessment section in this Information Pack).Security Clearance - The preferred applicants will be required to successfully undergo the security clearance vetting process at a specified clearance level. The preferred applicant MUST be willing to disclose all relevant and required information.Organisational AssessmentAn Organisational Assessment is a mandatory requirement for work in ASD. Organisational assessments are conducted to determine suitability to work in a high-security environment and to hold the appropriate security clearance for the role. You must obtain and maintain the nominated security clearance to work in ASD.The assessment is administered in a manner that ensures informed consent, fair dealing with all applicants and employees, and the greatest possible degree of privacy and transparency of process. Before you submit an application you should consider your own preparedness for questions that may include the following topics: personal relationships, living circumstances, personal values, financial situation, physical and mental health history, including substance use, and any civil and/or military record.FeedbackIf you are currently employed in the Australian Intelligence Community or the ADF, you will be provided with feedback on your Organisational Assessment, if the outcome has an adverse bearing on your current employment. No feedback will be provided on the outcome of the organisational assessment process to any other applicant.

teaser: Opportunity for a seasoned Software Engineer using a range of technologies working with a variety of new up and coming business's
desktopAdTemplate: Not sure if your next challenge looks like working on multiple projects to gain a wider breadth of experience or work in a product company to dive deeper into a problem domain? Well, just like the little girl from Old El Paso said, “Why not both?” We’re teaming up with an incredible Brisbane based Innovation Incubator business focusing on data related solutions with a UNIQUE twist. This team of creative thinkers and problem solvers work closely with industry expert founders needing technical guidance to solve challenges within their domain - and this team do it bloody well. To date they’ve worked on solving building applications for GPs to manage better patient outcomes for COVID, to solutions that allows the non-verbal community to have an augmented and alternative communication platform with lifelike speech synthesis. They spin out roughly 5 new product companies per year across a variety of industries from travel, health, medical to finance and everything in between. The most interesting part with this role is if the solution you build grows legs, matures and solves a problem in an area of interest to you, you’ll have the opportunity to move internally into that product company that is housed in the same building. Think of it as being part of a family that continues to grow under the same roof, where your partners success means your success. Pretty cool, huh?The deeper dive into what the gig looks like The role will involve you working closely with industry leading founders as part of a squad-based team consisting of a delivery lead, designers, engineers, analysts and data scientist. The first 3 months of engagement typically consist of discovery phase that is design led, working initially large amounts of uncertainty to ascertain what the problem is, who the product will be used by and designing a solution in a RAD methodology. In this role you’ll be providing technical leadership for early stage products, getting your hands dirty with code contribution and quality and recommend alternative solutions if the product needs to take a different direction.The technical Ideally, we’re looking for a programming language agnostic engineer (to use the term, polyglot) who likes to use the right tools to get the job done. If you’ve worked with one or more of these languages, you’re the right person! Their primary tech stack generally consists of:Front end with React and mobile React Native (open if you’ve worked with Vue or Angular) Back end with Node, Python, Java, .NET and Go Infrastructure on Azure, GCP and AWS What you can expect in returnFlexible 3 days WFH arrangement Continual professional and personal development with in-house coaches including directors of the business Ability to grow into a product company start-up that interests you If this has slightly interested you on the surface, there’s more to love about this and I’m keen to share that with you over a chat via details below! Daniel Belic 0407 903 686 Daniel.belic@affix.com.au

teaser: An opportunity to impact strategic decision-making in Defence and the Australian Government with respect to emerging technologies.
desktopAdTemplate: The Role:The Joint and Operations Analysis Division (JOAD) in Defence Science and Technology Group is offering several ongoing positions at the S&T3/4 Level (APS5/6). These positions are all in the Strategy and Joint Force (SJF) Major S&T Capability (MSTC) within JOAD, with a range of skills and experience being required.The following positions, all located in Canberra ACT, are available: Strategic Futures Analyst Data ScientistEmerging Technology Analyst – Economic impactsEmerging Technology Analyst – Social impactsDue to the diverse skills and responsibilities for these roles, applicants are strongly encouraged to look at the individual position descriptions prior to putting together their application. Each position description will describe in more detail the role and subsequently what Defence sees as an ideal candidate for each. About our Team:Strategy and Joint Force (SJF) Major Science and Technology Capability (MSTC) is within the Joint and Operations Analysis Division of Defence Science and Technology Group (DSTG). DST has set up a new Critical Technology Foresight Science and Technology Capability (STC) which has resulted from the establishment of the whole of government Critical Technology Policy Coordination Office (CTPCO), for which DST is leading the technology foresight function. This team works closely with the existing Defence Impacts of Emerging Technologies STC. Between them, the two teams will provide technology foresight support to Defence, National Security agencies and advice on potential critical technologies for whole of government. Our Ideal Candidate:These positions require a demonstrated understanding of the factors influencing S&T research and development, and its strategic relevance to the national interest. A successful candidate will have the ability to:  Recognise technology opportunities for the long-term benefit of Australia – including whole-of-government, Defence and National Security; and Use scientific judgment to analyse options, make decisions and prioritise research areas to maximise stakeholder outcomes.As the ideal candidate you will be able to:  Use your specialised knowledge and research experience in a relevant scientific area to generate new knowledge and produce enhanced capabilities for clients and sponsors.Build and maintain effective professional networks and relationships with clients and stakeholders across Defence, industry, academia and other research agencies.Lead the development of Science & Technology (S&T) initiatives Innovate and problem solve independently.Develop strategies to achieve task milestones and organisational outcomes.Contribute towards ongoing self-improvement and professional development.Application Closing Date: Thursday 5 August, 2021For further information please review the job information pack, reference DSTG/03181/21, on www.defence.gov.au/apscareers
