The following are examples of some of the work you could apply your technical expertise to: IT Systems  Communications: digital and analogue, fixed and mobile wireless, satellite, antenna design Engineer and maintain international communication networks Design and program software solutions using a variety of programming languages such as C/C++, Java or Python to solve unique problems Microelectronics: VHDL, FPGA, microelectronic manufacturing and testing (MCM, SOC) electronic packaging, VLSI Network engineering: design and analysis of LANs/WANs, routers, switches, firewalls, protocols Perform testing, systems integrations and deploy mission-critical systems Systems engineering:  end-to-end real-time operating systems, signals processing, VHDL/hardware development. Build and run high-performance super-computers Design and implement container based application solutions using Docker and Kubernetes based platform services Communicate closely with customers and provide expertise to support complex and critical projects Carry out computer forensics  Collect and exploit target communications Network design and risk management Offensive cyber operations Respond to incidents on critical networks Reverse engineering Vulnerability analysisSoftware Development & Engineering Software engineering: Java, C++, Perl, Python, Ruby, PowerShell, XML, HTML, web applications, object-oriented analysis and design, rapid prototyping, algorithm development PHP, Python, JavaScript frameworks, user interface development, open source plugin/module development Cloud/container infrastructure design for high-availability enterprise information applications, including continuous deployment from Git managed code in OpenStack, AWS and Azure environments. Working knowledge of Containers/Kubernetes deployments.Multimedia & Publishing Services Audio Visual Specialists scoping, designing, installing, and testing complex audio visual systems across the organisation and across the country. Graphic Design Specialists liaising with stakeholders from across the organisation to provide high-level graphic design services using Adobe Design Suite software. Multimedia Specialists using editing and publication development software to develop audio and visual productions and to assist with the development of multimedia learning presentations across ASD. Content Developers and Editors providing high-quality structural editing, copyediting and proofreading to ensure ASD’s written communications are professionally presented, can be clearly interpreted, are accurate, grammatically correct, and comply with accessibility legislative requirements. ICT Word Template Development Specialists creating and maintaining corporate Word templates using VBA and XML coding in compliance with ASD and Commonwealth documentation and branding standards, while maintaining visual consistency and functionality across ASD’s corporate documents. Printing Officers using complex and computer-driven, industrial-scale printers and associated equipment to conduct publishing, printing and reprographic tasks and activities in accordance with ASD standards. Web design and web content authoring, editing, publishing and review as well as web service life-cycle management.ICT Customer Support Officers Liaise with a diverse range of personnel across the Intelligence Community to provide support, respond to customer requests and provide timely advice and information. Use application management software and tools to manage ICT requests and incidents. Identify automation that improves the end user experience. Provide 1st level incident response, identify workarounds and resolve problems. Analyse data, assess business workflows and procedures and communicate recommendations to management for process improvement. Manage team roles and activities for service management processes and functions.Data Science, Analytics & Engineering  Develop new and innovative data analytics. Provide support for security operations functions and database technologies such as SQL, Maria DB and PostgreQSL. Determine questions that need to be answered by developing hypotheses, gathering, organising and cleaning raw data. Apply algorithms in order to explore, analyse and interpret patterns in the data. Create data-driven solutions for identified problems and issues, and communicate the results to a wide variety of personnel and stakeholders.Information Security  Computer and network security Cryptographic services Incident response Penetration testing Vulnerability analysis 895 IT security threat assessments, policy and adviceSystem Architects Assess the integrity and integration of information from all available sources through the application of a variety of analytical and presentation techniques. Assess operational requirements, problems and opportunities, seeking effective business solutions through improvements in new or changed processes. Evaluate and appraise architectures based on evidence and assessments to ensure compliance with agreed procedures. Develop models and plans to implement or influence strategy to improve business performance. Develop and maintain architectural artefacts to support mission objectives. Identify and assess the relevance and risk of new and emerging hardware and software technologies and products to support ASD’s ICT strategies.Systems Administrators Design, manage, integrate and ensure system integrity and performance tuning and monitoring across data processing, collaboration and communication applications including Splunk, ELK, Microsoft SCSM, SharePoint and the Atlassian suite. Perform routing installation, patching, upgrading and uninstallation of operating systems and application software. Contribute to the design, development, testing, implementation, documentation, support, security, maintenance or enhancement of ASD's communication and processing systems. Use experience in change management to maintain the continuity of capability delivered by IT operations and business functions. Provide Automated Configuration Management activities using Puppet, Salt, Ansible Azure Devops, Kubenetes and/or container management tools. Design, manage and integrate desktop physical and virtual systems. Design, deploy and support Windows desktop solutions on physical, and, virtual VMWare and Citrix platforms. Solve issues for unpredictable problems and establish operating policies, procedures and documentation.ASD continues to grow and is continually looking for talented people to join our mission. This will be a rolling-recruitment process, which means it will be conducted regularly. desktopAdTemplate: Do you wish you could use your cultural and language expertise to help protect Australia’s interests and play a role in Australia’s response to strategic threats?Would you like to combine your language expertise with other skills in a multidisciplinary role?ASD is looking for people from all backgrounds with expertise in Languages Other than English (LOTE), with ranging levels of experience, to fill a diverse range of roles across the breadth of ASD activities. These range from highly specialised LOTE roles to multidisciplinary roles with a LOTE component. The work we do is unique, critical and incredibly rewarding.We are interested in a wide range of languages. Our current priorities are languages of Northeast and Southeast Asia, the Pacific, and the Middle East/Central Asian region.We are looking for applicants with the ability to think critically, who are motivated to continue to learn and develop their skills.Ideal candidates will be innovative, team orientated and have a passion for operating, building or supporting strategically important ASD capabilities.Regardless of the role, we want people who are able to work within a team environment and use their curiosity, resilience and creativity to solve problems involved in out-thinking and out-imagining some of the most testing adversaries.In return you can expect extensive training and ongoing support to further develop your LOTE skills to meet the changing demands of ASD activities.You will have the opportunity to apply your LOTE skills, in combination with your other skills, experience and interests, in roles across the organisation such as: Signals Intelligence Analyst Foreign Language Analyst Signals Intelligence Technologist Cyber Threat Analyst Intrusion Analyst Intelligence Assessment Analyst Learning and Development Officer Customer Service Officer Data Scientist / Data AnalystASD continues to grow and is always looking for talented people to join its mission. The following are examples of some of the different roles and tasks in which you could apply your LOTE expertise and other skills. Your role may include just one task on the list, or may involve aspects of several: Signals Intelligence Analyst/Foreign Language Analyst/Technologist Roles translate or interpret materials in languages other than English analyse and report on materials in languages other than English develop capabilities to perform your analysis using software development skills develop new methods of analysing and exploiting data for intelligence or information security purposes investigate large and complex data sets plan and conduct offensive cyber operations, including covert online operations prepare short-term or long-term information reports to governmentCyber Security Roles conduct cyber security research, analysis, and strategic threat assessments perform detailed cyber event analysis, intelligence assessments, and professional and policy advice for identified cyber threats plan, coordinate and conduct proactive cyber threat discovery assess and evaluate cyber threat intelligence for indicators of compromise  provide detailed planning, analysis and reporting on current and emerging threats to information systems.Learning and Development/Customer Service Roles perform analysis, design, development, conduct and evaluation of LOTE learning and development activities select and manage the provision of external LOTE learning and development services maintain and contribute to the delivery of high quality LOTE customer service activities understand and advise stakeholders of LOTE-related products and services liaise with internal and external stakeholders to understand and meet needs and expectations recommend solutions to issues and problems identified in LOTE processes and workflowsData Science and Data Analysis Roles use your understanding of language to extract knowledge from data perform computational analysis of linguistically complex datasets provide advice on the selection of data science tools work as a member of a multi-disciplinary team providing data services to stakeholders contribute to the development, evaluation, monitoring and deployment of machine learning and computer assisted translation systemsASD continues to grow and is continually looking for talented people to join our mission.This will be a rolling-recruitment process, which means it will be conducted regularly. If you are successful in the application and assessment process you will be placed in a merit pool and may be contacted for further testing as positions become available. These may be ongoing or non-ongoing opportunities.Throughout the year, ASD may contact you to reconfirm your interest in roles and update you with any relevant information. We request that you also let us know if your circumstances change and you no longer wish to remain in the merit pool. Qualifications / Experience Requirements ASD is looking for people with high level skills in a range of languages other than English. Our current priority regions include Northeast Asia, Southeast Asia, the Pacific and Middle East/Central Asia. We are interested in native and heritage language speakers, as well as those who have studied languages. A university qualification, NAATI accreditation or Australian Government language testing result would be highly desirable, but not essential.  We welcome applicants who have specialised in languages, as well as those who combine their language skills with other capabilities such as technical, training, graphic design and multimedia, or analytical skills. If you don’t have an existing government qualification, you will be tested on your LOTE skills during the assessment process. This may include automated online and/or assessment centre testing, and may include testing of reading comprehension, listening comprehension and/or translation skills. These range from highly specialised LOTE roles to multidisciplinary roles with a LOTE component. The work we do is unique, critical and incredibly rewarding.We are interested in a wide range of languages. Our current priorities are languages of Northeast and Southeast Asia, the Pacific, and the Middle East/Central Asian region.We are looking for applicants with the ability to think critically, who are motivated to continue to learn and develop their skills.Ideal candidates will be innovative, team orientated and have a passion for operating, building or supporting strategically important ASD capabilities.Regardless of the role, we want people who are able to work within a team environment and use their curiosity, resilience and creativity to solve problems involved in out-thinking and out-imagining some of the most testing adversaries.In return you can expect extensive training and ongoing support to further develop your LOTE skills to meet the changing demands of ASD activities.You will have the opportunity to apply your LOTE skills, in combination with your other skills, experience and interests, in roles across the organisation such as: Signals Intelligence Analyst Foreign Language Analyst Signals Intelligence Technologist Cyber Threat Analyst Intrusion Analyst Intelligence Assessment Analyst Learning and Development Officer Customer Service Officer Data Scientist / Data AnalystASD continues to grow and is always looking for talented people to join its mission. The following are examples of some of the different roles and tasks in which you could apply your LOTE expertise and other skills. Your role may include just one task on the list, or may involve aspects of several: Signals Intelligence Analyst/Foreign Language Analyst/Technologist Roles translate or interpret materials in languages other than English analyse and report on materials in languages other than English develop capabilities to perform your analysis using software development skills develop new methods of analysing and exploiting data for intelligence or information security purposes investigate large and complex data sets plan and conduct offensive cyber operations, including covert online operations prepare short-term or long-term information reports to governmentCyber Security Roles conduct cyber security research, analysis, and strategic threat assessments perform detailed cyber event analysis, intelligence assessments, and professional and policy advice for identified cyber threats plan, coordinate and conduct proactive cyber threat discovery assess and evaluate cyber threat intelligence for indicators of compromise  provide detailed planning, analysis and reporting on current and emerging threats to information systems.Learning and Development/Customer Service Roles perform analysis, design, development, conduct and evaluation of LOTE learning and development activities select and manage the provision of external LOTE learning and development services maintain and contribute to the delivery of high quality LOTE customer service activities understand and advise stakeholders of LOTE-related products and services liaise with internal and external stakeholders to understand and meet needs and expectations recommend solutions to issues and problems identified in LOTE processes and workflowsData Science and Data Analysis Roles use your understanding of language to extract knowledge from data perform computational analysis of linguistically complex datasets provide advice on the selection of data science tools work as a member of a multi-disciplinary team providing data services to stakeholders contribute to the development, evaluation, monitoring and deployment of machine learning and computer assisted translation systemsASD continues to grow and is continually looking for talented people to join our mission.This will be a rolling-recruitment process, which means it will be conducted regularly. If you are successful in the application and assessment process you will be placed in a merit pool and may be contacted for further testing as positions become available. These may be ongoing or non-ongoing opportunities.Throughout the year, ASD may contact you to reconfirm your interest in roles and update you with any relevant information. We request that you also let us know if your circumstances change and you no longer wish to remain in the merit pool. Qualifications / Experience Requirements ASD is looking for people with high level skills in a range of languages other than English. Our current priority regions include Northeast Asia, Southeast Asia, the Pacific and Middle East/Central Asia. We are interested in native and heritage language speakers, as well as those who have studied languages. A university qualification, NAATI accreditation or Australian Government language testing result would be highly desirable, but not essential.  We welcome applicants who have specialised in languages, as well as those who combine their language skills with other capabilities such as technical, training, graphic design and multimedia, or analytical skills. If you don’t have an existing government qualification, you will be tested on your LOTE skills during the assessment process. This may include automated online and/or assessment centre testing, and may include testing of reading comprehension, listening comprehension and/or translation skills. Eligibility  Please ensure that you meet the eligibility requirements outlined in this Information Pack before submitting an application. Citizenship - To be eligible for employment with ASD, applicants must be an Australian citizen. Health Assessment - The preferred applicants may be required to undergo a medical examination conducted by the Agency’s preferred medical provider. Organisational Assessment – To be eligible for employment within ASD, the preferred applicants will be required to undergo an Organisational Assessment (see Organisational Assessment section in this Information Pack). Security Clearance - The preferred applicants will be required to successfully undergo the security clearance vetting process at a specified clearance level. The preferred applicant MUST be willing to disclose all relevant and required information. Organisational Assessment  An Organisational Assessment is a mandatory requirement for work in ASD. Organisational assessments are conducted to determine suitability to work in a high-security environment and to hold the appropriate security clearance for the role. You must obtain and maintain the nominated security clearance to work in ASD. The assessment is administered in a manner that ensures informed consent, fair dealing with all applicants and employees, and the greatest possible degree of privacy and transparency of process. Before you submit an application you should consider your own preparedness for questions that may include the following topics: personal relationships, living circumstances, personal values, financial situation, physical and mental health history, including substance use, and any civil and/or military record. Feedback If you are currently employed in the Australian Intelligence Community or the ADF, you will be provided with feedback on your Organisational Assessment, if the outcome has an adverse bearing on your current employment. No feedback will be provided on the outcome of the organisational assessment process to any other applicant.

About Us  Rich Data Corporation is a rapidly expanding, dynamic start-up based in Sydney. We use data and predictive analytics combined with artificial intelligence technology with deep knowledge in behaviour analysis to deliver innovative lending solutions for financial services and adjacent industries through our Delta platform.  We've signed contract with major banks in Australia (https://www.afr.com/companies/financial-services/nab-turns-to-artificial-intelligence-to-assess-small-business-loans-20201204-p56kmk).  After the recent VC investment, our value reached at US$53M. See  https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:6808014983138549760/     Our vision is to enable lenders to innovate and achieve highly profitable lending outcomes while providing inclusive credit options to consumers and SME.      Why Join Us?  This is an opportunity to join an organisation with a global footprint that is still small enough to be agile. Work with the leadership team to help drive the future of credit. Work with our world class research team to productise cutting edge AI innovations. Dynamic and friendly working environment. Our office is based in North Sydney with a great view overlooking the harbour. Competitive salary, $100,000 - $150,000 based on experience.   About the role  As the Senior Developer it’s essential that you are able to see the "big picture" as you’ll be taking the lead in designing, coding, testing and providing architecture direction from design choices to technical standards.     In this role you will be working on the design, development and implementation of financial services solutions using your advanced Java or Python experience combined with AI and Machine Learning algorithms provided by our Data scientist.     Key accountabilities Assume technical responsibility for all stages of the software development lifecycle. Design and develop specifications and solutions with attention to system integration and data management. Provide technical guidance and coaching to the development team from conception to deployment.Key challenges Design and implement complex solutions. Work with clients and teams distributed across multiple time zones. Constantly evaluate, learn and apply new technologies and new development techniques.   Skills & experience Strong knowledge of and practical software development experience in Java and Spring frameworks including Spring Boot, Spring Cloud for commercial production systems. Strong knowledge of application architecture and design principles including API design, REST, WS-*, SOA, Microservices, OOP, SOLID. In-depth knowledge and experience with data modelling and database design of relational and NoSQL database systems. Understanding of software quality assurance principles with experience implementing automated testing platforms and unit tests, Test Driven Development (TDD) and other agile methodologies. Interest in exploring new programming paradigms, languages, and patterns and a passion for growing your skills, tackling interesting work and challenging problems. Outstanding communication and presentation abilities. Python & AI/ML skills are highly regarded. DevOps and AWS experience is highly regarded. Full stack with Angular is highly regarded.   Apply Now!  If you have the relevant skills and are ready to take the next step in your career please apply via SEEK with your resume and cover letter attached!  Email: junlong.zhai@richdataco.com     Please note candidates must have Australian working rights  \

One of Australia's largest financial institutions is looking for a strong Data Scientist who can deliver best in class customer and industry initiatives, strives for operational excellence and can wrangle data as well as they can people. This is a great opportunity to create and manage a team of strong Data Science professionals, while also paving the way by use of all the latest cloud technologies.  About this Opportunity: Create and manage a team of Data Scientists who will assist you in achieving your goals.Create analytics tools and models to evaluate initiatives and ensure their outcomes.Generate insights from data gathered in multiple large resources.Solve complex business challenges using data.Embed the use of cloud technologies across the organisation.  About you: Predictive and financial modelling experience.Able to effectively translate data insights, and related actionable insights, to senior stakeholders.Machine Learning experience, using tech such as Python, R, and/or SQL.Visualisation experience with PowerBI and/or Tableau.Able to perform sourcing, cleansing, joining and ETL of data.   If this sounds like you, don't hesitate to apply now! Data Science is a fast-paced world, and this opportunity certainly won't last long! Hope to hear from you soon.Salt is acting as an Employment Agency in relation to this vacancy.

Data is explodingThe demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of first-class data analysts and data scientists.If you are passionate about data, we have the best way to get you into your new data career. How does it work?The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx. In addition, you will be trained by our team of experts in all the soft skills needed to become an outstanding consultant.The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career. Do I get paid to learn?Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience. Key datesThe Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round in Sydney are April, August and November.The applications for the November 2021 intake close on the 27th of September, 2021  What’s in it for you  Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technologyBecome a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platformIt’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultantGain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in AustraliaLearn from the best data and analytics experts in AustraliaStudy in a creative work space in central SydneyDetails of the role    Four months of classroom trainingFour client engagements, each 6 months longThe result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second yearWe’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in AustraliaWhen you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to youWhat we’re looking for   Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience. What we are looking for is:Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every dayData-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomesTech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy itCuriosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and whyResourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re askingFast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this roleCreativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible formsApplication ProcessWe do things differently and we’re proud of it. So forget about the application process you might be used to.Here’s how the process works:Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us!The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the applicationWe are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

Are you a Data Scientist Team Leader looking for a career role where you can place your stamp on the way data is viewed in a leading edge product that is used around the globe? You will work on the next generation of the product that is cloud based which orchestrates and monitors mining operations utilising autonomous mining equipment created by this organisation. Your work will provide real-time insight of mining operations and improve operational efficiencies.  The role is 50% Mentor / Leadership and 50% hands on building solutions. Specific Responsibilities include: Hands on developing and delivering data solutions through the full lifecycle in collaboration with several software and data teams alongside a small team of data scientists Leverage your working knowledge of best practices in data focused solutions, proactive research into emerging trends, intimate understanding of market context and your own network of advisors to inform the strategy Identify gaps and innovative solutions to bridge any capability gaps and update your catalogue of Data Science services accordingly Mentor a team of indirect reports of 2-3 data scientists and provide significant contribution to the development and implementation of the Data Science Roadmap      Required Skills and Experiences: Proven track record delivering Data Science solutions with material commercial benefit You will have extensive experience solving analytical problems through quantitative approaches and machine learning methods You are very familiar with standard tools for clustering, dimensionality reduction, regression, and classification. You have a flexible and pragmatic approach to technology and are proficient in Python or R (or both!) and ideally have strong experience in using languages, such as Java, C#, or shell scripts. Good experience on Cloud environments including Azure, Google, AWS Experience with leadership and mentoring roles in Data Science Ability to work within a product development group      Desired Skills and Experience (any of the following): Advanced degree in a relevant discipline in Statistics, Machine Learning, Mathematics, Actuarial Studies, Computer Science, Economics, or any other related quantitative field Any experience on ML Pipelines & MLOps (DevOps for Machine Learning), Data Factory, Data Lake, Databricks & Power BI. Experience with fleet management or vehicle monitoring systems  Experience in mining, civil engineering or surveying industry.  Pytorch and/or Tensorflow experience Deep Learning and Signal Processing   General Skills:Strong communication skills working with local and remote teams with the ability to assimilate knowledge from multiple sources Customer and quality focused  Self-motivated  Eye for detail  Agile mindset  Problem solving and troubleshooting   An attractive remuneration package is on offer including 12% super, annual performance bonus and the ability to buy discounted shares of the organisation. You'll be initially working from home 4 days per week and 1 day per week in the office. The office is based in the Brisbane CBD. The role requires that candidates have Australian PR/Citizenship or NZ Citizenship.For further details call Fortunato (aka Forty) Galluzzo on 043 870 9417.

$120,000 - $160,000As we at Rich Data Co strengthen our R&D to deliver cutting edge AI native products to our clients in banking and finance, we are hiring a Client Facing Data Scientist/Analyst. We are looking for an experience data scientist/analyst with at least 6 years of experience in delivering end to end data science initiatives to internal/external clients. You will develop predictive models, prepare analytics design documentation and communicate the insights to our clients.Our R&D innovate building the bridge between novel AI/ML and real-world business problem, specifically in business lending. For example, within credit risk domain, we build Teachable Glass-Box AI, Accumulative Intelligence using transfer learning and we combine expert knowledge with machine learning. We collaborate with leading academics in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning from top universities. Our clients are lending institutions and banks. Key Responsibilities:Documenting and presenting Data Science initiatives to our clients, both technical and non-technical executives.Design use case objective and success criteria, matching our capabilities and client needs.Develop data processing solutions and predictive models to address the business objective of our clients.Lead discovery engagement and develop prototypes to be deployed on the client platform.Support pre-sales, sales and client advisory team to deliver the expected business outcome. Qualifications:At least 6 years of experience as a Data Scientist, Data Analyst or Consultant, preferably in credit risk for business lending.Degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Artificial Intelligence or Statistics, post graduate degree in relevant field preferred. In your job application, please attached transcripts for your undergraduate degree (and postgraduate degree if you have ones)Comfortable with presenting and leading technical discussions.Fluency with all aspects of data science/data analytics including data pre-processing, feature construction/selection and hyperparameter tuning.Hand-on coder in Python/Pandas/Scikit-learn.Experience working with external clients. Why work with us:You will work with a highly intelligent team in Artificial Intelligence/Machine learning.You will learn and may invent novel AI algorithms.Our working environment is flexible.We pay above average remuneration.

The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking for individuals with a passion for data to join our Data Strategy, Integration and Services Division.We have several roles available to full-time and part-time applicants in our Canberra, Melbourne and Adelaide offices at an APS5 and APS6 level. About the role and areaWe are looking for people with a passion for data to fill a number of Data Professional roles including Data Engineer, Data Scientist, Data Security Adviser and Project Support Officer roles.Data Engineer responsibilities include:setup and testing of data provider management systems, data collection instruments, data warehouses, data pipelines and data processing systemscleaning and editing microdatatransforming data into a more valuable format by classifying and coding data; integrating datasets; aggregating data; and deriving new data itemsundertaking quality assurance of datasets (e.g. through macro-editing)confidentialising microdata to enable its safe use by external customers.Data Scientist responsibilities include:discovering, experimenting with and wrangling data, as well as leading the use of new data sources, methods and products to meet the changing information needs of customersbeing innovative and experimenting with new methods, algorithms, codes and programs, and thinking of different ways to solve problems that may not be refined or well-developedapplying a combination of software programming skills and statistical skillscommunicating and presenting findings to upskill others to use new techniques or methods and impart lessons learned.Data Security Adviser responsibilities include:providing advice and guidance on the application of government data security requirements and practices in data-driven programsidentifying and managing data security risks, balancing security requirements with operational and compliance needsadministering the daily operations of secure data environments, including user access and support requestsestablishing, building and maintaining highly effective working relationships with internal and external stakeholders.Project Support Officer responsibilities include:developing and maintaining relationships with external customers and internal data usersclearly defining and specifying the data needs of customerssupporting the management of a project including scheduling, risk management and documenting processescoordinating agreements and undertakings enabling their customers’ safe and effective access to microdata.Further Information:  To read more about these roles and/or to apply, select “Apply now”.  Applications close 11:30 PM AEST, Sunday 31st October.

Track record of scientific publications.

Experience in medical device design, development and regulatory requirements.

We are looking for a savvy Data Engineer/ Business Intelligence Engineer to join our growing team of analytics experts. You will expand and optimise our data and data pipeline architecture, as well as optimise data flow and collection for cross functional teams. The ideal candidate is an experienced data pipeline builder and data wrangler who enjoys optimising data systems and building them from the ground up. This will depend on your experience but a guide is $160K-$170K + 10% super.

Data is explodingThe demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. The starting dates for each round in Melbourne is February, June, October.The applications for the February 2022 intake close on the 6th December, 2021 What’s in it for you  Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technologyBecome a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platformIt’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultantGain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in AustraliaLearn from the best data and analytics experts in AustraliaStudy in a creative workspace in central MelbourneDetails of the role    Four months of classroom trainingFour client engagements, each 6 months longThe result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second yearWhen you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to youWe’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you have full working rights for AustraliaWhat we’re looking for   Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience. Operational Data Analyst  
 


Thinking about furthering your career in the Medical Devices industry and having a direct impact on patient outcomes?  
 


Do you have a passion for Data, Technological innovation, helping patients and building lasting relationships?  
 


Then look no further! 
 


The role: 
 
My client is seeking an Operational Data Analyst to provide data analytics support to their global field operations.  
 


The team is made up of world-class engineers, clinicians, and seasoned professionals with experience in bringing medical technologies to life.  
 


In this role you will be working closely with key stakeholders to understand business questions and collaborate with cross-functional teams (e.g. data engineers, data scientist, machine learning engineers, analysts) to execute data analytics projects that deliver business solutions. 
 


What a day will look like:  
 


Serve as the hub for data requests from their global Field Teams (primarily European and Australian teams). 
 


Design, create and maintain up-to-date patient data dashboards, reports and visualisations for Field team case review meetings and external presentations. 
 


Ensure data integrity by managing and monitoring entry, validation, and analysis of patient device data from a wide range of data sources, including medical devices and clinical studies. 
 


Conduct exploratory and statistical analysis on relevant data sources to meet stakeholder needs and improve patient outcomes. 
 


What you will need to be successful:  
 


At minimum, a technical bachelor’s degree in Biomedical Engineering/Biological Sciences/Software/Electrical/Mathematics or related discipline. 
 


2+ years of relevant commercial / industry analytics experience (Additional research experience highly regarded.) 
 


Intermediate to advanced Python programming skills, applied in a commercial environment. 
 


Intermediate database development and manipulation skills, applied in a commercial environment. 
 


Demonstrated experience designing, creating and using data visualisation and dashboarding tools to support data-driven commercial decisions using Power BI.  


 


Sound like you? 


 


Then we would love to chat with you about this and other Data Analyst opportunities.  
 


Either hit apply, or reach out to Ailbhe McDonagh Kelly at The Onset on 0481346579 or ailbhe@theonset.com.au

The Company 

 

This well-known and respected furniture and interior retailer has 56 stores spread across Australia and New Zealand and is widely recognised for their extensive range of desirable, built-to-last furniture, homewares, and lighting. The brand endeavours to cater to a wide variety of tastes, from distinguished modern-day classics to unique contemporary pieces, creating living environments that people love to be in.

 

The company’s product offering has evolved over its 35-year history however core values have remained the same; reflected in the continued importance placed on providing customers with a relaxed and friendly experience, a distinguished and quality product at a good price, and the highest level of service and aftercare. Along with working hard to meet customer’s needs, there is a very notable display of passion among employees, with a unique sense of connectedness to the company, and a genuine level of excitement for the next phase of planned growth.

 

The company’s board, executive, and management team have established a detailed 5-year strategic plan; and to deliver on this plan, a number of key senior appointments are required, of which the Data Scientist in one.

 The Role 
Reporting to the Head of Financial Planning & Analysis and working closely with Commercial Analysts, this is a hands on role (no direct reports) that will see you partnering with department GM’s across Marketing, CRM, Product, IT, Finance and Store Operations, to implement financial systems, processes, practices and reporting functions; whereby commercial decision making is well supported by meaningful data.

As the business embarks on a transformational brand journey, your role will play a particularly important part in using data to identify opportunities, optimise marketing activity and spend, to improve overall business growth and performance, within a multifaceted retail environment.

Your highly analytical mind and experience managing complex structures of data will assist in dissecting a problem into logical and workable components, identifying and weighing up several solutions, determining any road blocks, and assisting GM’s with balanced information to take the most effective course of action.

Your ability to interpret levels of performance against hypotheses, and confirm or deny correlation, while taking a bigger picture holistic viewpoint, and effectively conveying information to stakeholders, will allow you to make your mark in this high growth environment.

 ResponsibilitiesOrganising and manipulating data in Excel to be fit for purpose, using pivot tables, macros, statistics and formulas;Developing systems, processes, procedures and commercial reporting frameworks that supports a ‘one source of truth’ position;Identifying relevant data sources, collecting structured and unstructured data, setting up data infrastructure, data mining, sourcing missing data, organising data into usable formats, and building predictive models;Data enrichment and machine learning application to automate the identification of trends, patterns and behaviours, and analysing trends/patterns to find answers to specific questions;Processing, cleansing and verifying data – assessing quality of data and removing or cleaning data;Performing churn analytics, sentiment analysis (including data from voice and social/text), customer segmentation and life time value model development to support retail data science across end to end e-commerce, digital and B&M customer behaviour;Market share/cell analysis reporting;Full funnel customer journey forecasting and customer propensity modelling based on last touch points and purchase behaviours;Tracking and analysis of marketing performance (qualitative/quantitative, reach, ROI, etc) for both media and creative;Working with languages such as SQL, R or Python, and business intelligence software such as Power BI, to prepare, organise and display information in a powerful way;Creating visualisations of data and preparing reports for executive and project teams.Requirements Degree qualified in quantitative fields, such as Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Economics, Computing and Engineering;Expertise in management of complex structures of data;Possess strong analytical skills, mathematic abilities and business acumen;Possess critical thinking, a strong sense of discovery and curiosity, clear and open communication, relational and team building skills;Excellent written and verbal communication with the ability to share information and clearly identify and articulate the “SO WHAT” from all insights;Excellent knowledge of Office package, with advanced expertise in Excel (pivot, macros, statistics, formulas);Excellent knowledge of SQL;Knowledge of R or Python; nice to have knowledge of PowerBI, SSRS, Dataiku;Exceptional ability to forecast and in propensity modelling based on last touch points and purchase behaviours;Experience in Data mining, data enrichment, machine learning to automate the identification of trends/ patterns / behaviours;Retail experience essential.

 

While relevant experience is a must for this role, of equal importance is a good people and culture fit, and as such the successful candidate should also be able to demonstrate a broad range of attributes, such as excellent leadership, with a high degree of intellectual and strategic ability, while being comfortable with implementation. Seeking a collaborative team player who is straightforward, confident, low ego, team spirited and non-political, with a sense of fun, dynamism and enthusiasm and passion for excellence, innovation and delivery.
 Salary and Benefits  
This is a significant senior appointment, and the salary will reflect this, commensurate with experience.

 Applications

You will provide professional actuarial and policy advice in key technical areas and lead the development of innovative actuarial solutions in highly complex areas.Managing and developing client relationships will be critical to the success of the role, as will developing the work program for a team of actuarial analysts to ensure delivery of a key program of work and developing staff. Qualifications / Experience The successful applicant will be able to demonstrate experience delivering authoritative, insightful and practical actuarial advice to a diverse range of public sector clientsThe successful applicant will have:• well-developed consulting skills;• a capacity to contribute to broader strategies and initiatives;• experience in the actuarial analysis of public sector programs;• strong conceptual and analytical skills including the application of micro simulation and machine learning in actuarial or related fields; and• strong communication and interpersonal skills.Applicants will be Fellows of the Institute of Actuaries of Australia and/or demonstrate exceptional experience in related statistical areas. About IMDEXIMDEX is a leading global Mining-Tech company, which enables successful and cost-effective operations from exploration to production. At IMDEX we develop cloud-connected devices and drilling optimisation products to improve the process of identifying and extracting mineral resources for drilling contractors and resource companies globally… both in surface and underground mining applications.Join Our Exciting New Division – IMDEX Mining Technology (IMT)Part of our growth strategy is to extend new technologies into the mining market – including geophysical instrumentation, robotic operations and advanced data acquisition systems.A recent example is the IMDEX BLAST DOG™ for Drill & Blast applications which is an autonomous system that includes logging material characteristics of blast holes, which then allows automated spatial domaining of physical properties and fracturing based on high-resolution 3D material models and material tracking in the pit.The opportunityIMT is looking for an experience Data Scientist, to design, build, use and maintain custom data models. Data Scientist - NDARC
Employment Type: Full-time (35-hour week)
Duration: 12-month Fixed Term role
Remuneration: $99K - $125K (dependent on experience) plus 17% superannuation and leave loading
Location: Randwick NSW
Be part of a team that’s delivering change at scale
Join one of Australia’s Top 20 most attractive employers
Thrive on a campus that’s buzzing with the energy of people doing great things
UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. Yes, we’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community; a community doing great things. But what makes us different isn’t what we do, it’s how we do it. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do.
Why your role matters  
As the Data Scientist, you will be responsible for strengthening and expanding the study of novel online data sources to identify emerging trends in illicit drug use, markets and associated behaviours for the Drug Trends program at the National Drug and Alcohol Research Centre (NDARC). The role will include expanding existing monitoring and reporting on darknet cryptomarket sale of illicit drugs, establishing new reporting on other online sources (e.g., internet discussion forums, social media platforms such as Reddit and Twitter, search engines) and building online interactive visualisations to interrogate and share findings. Drawing upon an array of computational and statistical skills, you will collaborate with leading figures in this field to address critical public health questions in relation to substance use.
The Data Scientist reports to the Senior Research Fellow and has no direct reports. Please see attached  Position Description for full details.
Who you are 
To be successful you must have:
 Level 7:
Relevant degree specialising in computer science, mathematics, biostatistics, data science, statistics, or other quantitative discipline, with relevant experience or equivalent competence gained through any combination of education, training and experience.
Demonstrated experience in using Python for web scraping, data cleansing, and machine learning. Knowledge of other programming languages such as R would be advantageous.
Demonstrated experience in building, testing and deploying machine learning models (GLM, Random Forest, GBM, Neural networks etc).
Demonstrated experience in cleaning, merging, and managing large data sets, including implementing various strategies to maximise data integrity.
Demonstrated experience in building online data visualisation platforms (e.g., Tableau, R Shiny).
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with a high level of attention to detail.
An understanding of and commitment to UNSW’s aims, objectives and values in action, together with relevant policies and guidelines.
Knowledge of health and safety responsibilities and commitment to attending relevant health and safety training.
Level 8 (in addition to the above):
Doctoral degree in computer science, statistics, biostatistics, data science, mathematics, or other quantitative discipline, with substantial extension of the theories and principles normally requiring extensive relevant experience.
Demonstrated capacity to conceptualise novel research questions and carry out independent research as indicated by a proven track record of leading reports or manuscripts for publication in peer-reviewed journals.
Demonstrated evidence of bringing innovation and improvements in achieving core objectives and outputs.
Please apply online - applications will not be accepted if sent to the contact listed.
Contact (For job related queries only):
Jamie Cutler: Talent Acquisition Coordinator                     E: j.cutler@unsw.edu.au Applications close: Sunday 5th December at 11:55pm
Find out more about working at UNSW at https://med.unsw.edu.au/
UNSW aspires to be the exemplar Australian university and employer of choice for people from diverse backgrounds. UNSW aims to ensure equality in recruitment, development, retention and promotion of staff, and that no-one is disadvantaged on the basis of their gender, cultural background, disability, sexual orientation or identity. We encourage everyone who meets the selection criteria to apply.

Banking and Finance exp is highly regarded.Tertiary education in the Science, Technology, Engineering or Mathematics disciplines will be a big plus.Experience of using data mining, statistical methods and machine-learning techniquesProgramming experience across : ML, Python and SQLDemonstrated ability to navigate complexity and ambiguity to provide pragmatic commercial solutions, which meet stakeholder expectations.Track record of building effective relationships internally and externally with stakeholders, intermediaries and service providers.Excellent verbal and written communication skills, capable of communicating with audiences at all levels with clarity, impact and influence.This is a great opportunity to work with a market-leading brand that offers excellent training and development to support continuous learning and careers opportunities.Please apply on-line or for more information please contact Kausty Mahajan at Bluefin Resources on 02 9270 2603. Job Description  : Responsibilities for Hadoop DeveloperCreate and maintain optimal data pipeline architecture,Assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional / non-functional business requirements.Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability, etc.Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation, and loading of data from a wide variety of data sources using SQL and AWS ‘big data’ technologies.Build analytics tools that utilize the data pipeline to provide actionable insights into customer acquisition, operational efficiency and other key business performance metrics.Work with stakeholders including the Executive, Product, Data and Design teams to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs.Keep our data separated and secure across national boundaries through multiple data centers and AWS regions.Create data tools for analytics and data scientist team members that assist them in building and optimizing our product into an innovative industry leader.Work with data and analytics experts to strive for greater functionality in our data systems.will support our software developers, database architects, data analysts and data scientists on data initiatives and will ensure optimal data delivery architecture is consistent throughout ongoing projects. Technology Skills SQoop , Scala , Spark , ETL Tools , AWS (Amazon Web Services)

This is a mid-level Data Scientist opening within a very cool, high-impact strategy team part of a large ASX-listed company with millions of customers. For a junior-mid level data scientist, you would have amazing exposure to a strong mentor (lead data scientist), opportunities to work with cutting-edge big data and cloud tech (Apache Spark, GCP, dbt, Python, Airflow, etc) and importantly, solve challenging problems.      What does the team look like? This is a 4-5 person squad and you will work with a Lead Data Scientist, Senior Analyst & Data Visualisation specialist. There is a separate sister data science team who focus on customer loyalty, advertising, digital and e-commerce projects.      What kind of work does the team do? A mix of greenfield data science projects, ad hoc requests and projects and building and maintaining data science products. There is also a view that most, or all your work should be explainable. Not every project will be a huge ML model as sometimes you are answering critical or urgent questions for executive decisions, but these problems will tend to be very interesting and if there was not a key statistical or data science requirement, we wouldn’t be working on it.      What are some examples of projects I would work on?There is a new model being built to help solve challenging problems across different sites; how do we model the amount and shapes of retail space in each site and optimise this for new clients? Another project is helping migrate from Quantium transaction data (NAB) to the new Commbank IQ transaction data. Another stream of early work is exploring use of video data for analytics and insights to understand movement patterns       What skills and academic background is required for this data science role?A strong maths and statistics background is required – including ability to apply scientific thinking and experimentation to data. This would include an academic background such as a Masters or PhD level in a data science related field Good Python skills are required (we assume you have decent SQL or R also) as you will need to use various modelling packages, write scripts, contribute production-grade code and connect and integrate various cloud and big data services (they use Apache Spark and GCP – Google Cloud Platform) Confidence and strong communication skills with business stakeholders. This would extend beyond working with data peers to explaining models and advanced concepts to senior executives and workshopping ideas in cross-functional teams.       What would the first 6 months look like? Realistically, your first 6 months will include learning a lot about the existing software and data environment, Machine Learning pipelines, existing codebase and helping maintain, de-bug and productionise some models. There are some fairly large, complex models and it will be beneficial for you to understand these well (and also get to know the business!) before building greenfield data science products.    After 6 months is where you will start to see more interesting work and take some ownership of end-to-end solutions.      What kind of tools and tech stack will I work with on the job? The team currently use a lot of; Google BigQuery, Python, R, SQL, Airflow, Spark, dbt. Professional experience with more of these will help your application.    That said, this team works on solving questions that have not been solved before, so new innovative technologies will always be encouraged and adopted. It will help if you are motivated self-learner who enjoys exploring new tools and is happy to make recommendations to the team.      You haven’t mentioned reporting, BI and data visualization – is that part of the job? It may be a small portion, however, there is a visualization expert in the team and also other teams of BI and reporting specialists that handle normal or BAU work in this space.      Does this hire favour a data scientist from a Maths OR Programming background? Ideally some of both. The ability to work with big data, de-bug and contribute to production pipelines and understand concepts like scalability is important - so this won’t be a role where someone can learn Python on the job. If you come from a computer science or data mining background working in ML, then we will still need a strong analytical and statistical knowledge. If you have come from a pure maths or stats background into data science, then we would look for professional or side project experience demonstrating expertise writing clean code and working with data.      What are the other important job facts? This is a full-time, permanent role and the team is based in Sydney. You will need full-Australian work rights to be eligible and be able to work at least 2 or 3 days in the Sydney CBD office with the rest flexible, e.g. work from home.      What is the salary on offer? This depends on your experience. The guidance would be: $120K-$140K including super, with a bonus up to 20% on top.       More information and guidance will be provided to shortlisted candidates.

Data is explodingThe demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of first-class data analysts and data scientists.If you are passionate about data, we have the best way to get you into your new data career. How does it work?The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx. In addition, you will be trained by our team of experts in all the soft skills needed to become an outstanding consultant.The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career. Do I get paid to learn?Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience. Key datesThe Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round in Sydney are April, August and November.The applications for the April 2022 intake close on the 31st of January, 2022  What’s in it for you  Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technologyBecome a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platformIt’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultantGain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in AustraliaLearn from the best data and analytics experts in AustraliaStudy in a creative work space in central SydneyDetails of the role    Four months of classroom trainingFour client engagements, each 6 months longThe result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second yearWe’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in AustraliaWhen you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to youWhat we’re looking for   Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience. What we are looking for is:Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every dayData-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomesTech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy itCuriosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and whyResourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re askingFast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this roleCreativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible formsApplication ProcessWe do things differently and we’re proud of it. So forget about the application process you might be used to.Here’s how the process works:Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us!The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the applicationWe are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

A high impact opportunity for a Data Scientist has become available within the Strategic Decision Support team of ALDI Stores. This position is based at our National Office in Minchinbury, Western Sydney and is a full time permanent position, with work from home options.
Reporting to the national Data Science leader, the successful candidate will be fluent in data modelling and time series forecasting, in addition to possessing experience in utilising SQL, Python and/or R and visualisation methods to provide accurate forecasting insights to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.  
What's in it for you?  
Market leading remuneration $121,900 - $139,000 (including super)
5 weeks annual leave
10 days a month working from home
Be part of a growing, high performing business unit
Problem solving real business challenges in high impact areas
Role Responsibilities:
Creation of machine learning forecasting models and analysis to guide automated data-driven decision making
Drive insight-led analytics relating to the evaluation of ALDI product and strategy performance
Assist in forming business strategy by building analytical models that review and identify performance opportunities, providing insights and implications to relevant stakeholders
Collate, extract, cleanse and manage data from multiple sources to bring together insights and to ensure data integrity
Present findings to internal stakeholders while articulating key insights
Selection Criteria:
Master of Data Science or Graduate Certificate in Data Science required.
Demonstrated experience in Time Series  Forecasting, PCA, clustering, regression and classification
Python and/or R required
SQL experience required  (preferably Microsoft T-SQL)
Proficiency with Tableau or Power BI desirable (but not required)
Proficiency with Hadoop/MapReduce/DataBricks desirable (but not required)
Proficiency explaining how a machine learning model works to non-data scientists.
High attention to detail and accuracy
COVID-19 update
At ALDI we believe that our employees should expect to come to work every day with the comfort and confidence that they are in the safest possible environment. You will be required to adhere to all ALDI and State and Federal Government COVID-safe practices and regulations.
From March 1st 2022, a condition of ongoing employment with ALDI will be that employees are fully vaccinated against COVID-19 unless they have a valid medical exemption. This requirement will apply to all employees across stores, warehouse, transport and offices.

Overview of the Department:Be part of something bigger: contribute to building a secure Australia that is prosperous, open and united. Join a connected team of professionals, where you can be your authentic self; grow your career while making time for all parts of your life.The Department of Home Affairs is a central policy agency, providing coordinated strategy and policy leadership for Australia’s national and transport security, federal law enforcement, criminal justice, cyber security, border, immigration, multicultural affairs, emergency management and trade related functions. Overview of the Branch and Section: The Enterprise Analytics and Data Applications section and the newly established Data Science Capability section, in the Data Science Branch, provide operationally focused enterprise analytic capability and data science capability development. We work collaboratively across all border domains and the broader portfolio to continuously improve its data science capabilities with the aim to effectively inform and support decision makers. We use entrepreneurial approaches that embrace technological disruption to reshape and ‘future-proof’ Department’s capabilities. Our work is a key enabler of digital transformation within the Department through the application of technology, data, machine learning and artificial intelligence.We undertake research and development in the field of data science by applying new approaches, innovative techniques and technologies to departmental data. This includes developing and deploying end-to-end solutions in areas including, but not limited to, predictive analytics, computer vision, and natural language processing.Data Science Branch is committed to high standards or integrity and ethical responsibility. We are leading efforts to improve accountability and transparency throughout the lifecycle of our analytic capabilities. This includes taking active measures to assess and counteract analytic bias within artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) capabilities, ensuring high standards of integrity, and using data ethical and responsible manner.Workforce diversity is critical to performance in our field. We continue to build a diverse and inclusive workforce across gender, culture, religion, identity and life experience domains. We invest heavily in our people recognising the critical role empowered staff play in leading innovation.  About the role:There are several exciting opportunities in the section at the EL1 level for Senior Data Scientists working across different border domains including cargo, mail, trade, traveller and visa. You will develop and deliver analytical products to support business lines across the portfolio, including Visa Programme areas, Intelligence Division and the Australian Border Force (ABF) operations.Senior Data Scientists are technical specialists who work hands-on with data using a variety of specialised programming languages, software and systems to analyse and interpret large volumes of data. They apply advanced analytic techniques including supervised and unsupervised machine learning, deep learning, graph analytics, geospatial analytics, text mining and visualisation to solve complex business problems. Our ideal candidate:The branch is looking for people with strong analytical and problem solving skills who enjoy working with data and cutting edge technology. The ability to work well within a team, and to develop positive working relationships with others within and external to the Department is essential. You will be self-driven and have a commitment to innovation.Senior Data Scientists may have a tertiary degree in data science, mathematics, computer science or a related discipline, or relevant professional experience. They will have experience with the application of a range of data science and machine learning techniques and expertise in one or more programming languages. They will be able to take full ownership of the technical backlog, assigning tasks to data scientists and providing holistic technical guidance and leadership. They are held accountable for the success or failure of the projects they lead and can work with others to stay on schedule. Senior Data Scientists also mentor other data scientists and analysts and play a key role in advancing the data science discipline within the Department. Specific duties/responsibilities:Take full ownership the technical backlog, troubleshooting problem areas and leading investigation of potential solutionsWork effectively and collaboratively with key stakeholders and subject matter experts, understanding user needs, where there may be gaps and leading change across the company to adopt data science practicesApply analytical and critical thinking skills to understand the ‘big picture’ and where value for the business liesExplain work to both technical and non-technical audiences using excellent communication and collaboration skillsTake responsibility for projects and work well with others from different teams to drive a project to closureUndertake complex research in the application of data science techniques to address departmental business problemsDetect patterns and relationships in data using a range of statistical, predictive modelling, data mining and machine learning techniques to identify threats and risks;Build prescriptive analytics models to calculate expected business outcomes that support decision recommendations or decision automation and optimise business effectivenessProduce complex software program code/scripts to facilitate safe and secure data extraction and analyticsCoach and mentor junior data scientists, leading and working effectively with team members who are contributing to projects Applicant response:As part of your application, you will be required to prepare a response document (minimum 11pt font in MSWord or PDF format), which you will upload in the next section. Please ensure you read the instructions carefully, noting failure to address identified requirements may lead to your application being deemed ineligible.Please prepare a one-page Applicant Response in relation to the advertised role, outlining:how your skills, knowledge and experience will be relevant to this rolewhy you are interested in the role and what you can offer usany specific examples or achievements that demonstrate your ability to perform the role.
